WEBVTT

1
00:02:17.500 --> 00:02:21.002
Ow! Oh!

2
00:02:21.003 --> 00:02:24.164
Stop. stop. stop.

3
00:02:25.841 --> 00:02:27.717
Stop. Stop.

4
00:02:27.718 --> 00:02:29.844
No. Krypto. Krypto.

5
00:02:29.845 --> 00:02:31.964
Ow!

6
00:02:34.517 --> 00:02:36.809
Krypto.

7
00:02:36.810 --> 00:02:39.722
Take me home.

8
00:02:43.651 --> 00:02:44.852
Home.

9
00:02:57.540 --> 00:02:58.657
Krypto.

10
00:02:59.208 --> 00:03:00.993
Home.

11
00:03:44.128 --> 00:03:45.412
Superman!

12
00:04:00.728 --> 00:04:01.936
Thank you.

13
00:04:01.937 --> 00:04:05.356
No need to thank us. sir.
as we will not appreciate it.

14
00:04:05.357 --> 00:04:07.650
We have no consciousness whatsoever.

15
00:04:07.651 --> 00:04:10.653
Merely automatons. here to serve.

16
00:04:10.654 --> 00:04:13.357
Meet Twelve. She's new.

17
00:04:13.949 --> 00:04:17.034
- Hi.
- He looked at me.

18
00:04:17.035 --> 00:04:19.954
I put your parents'
message on to soothe you.

19
00:04:19.955 --> 00:04:21.031
Thank you.

20
00:04:21.123 --> 00:04:23.200
He finds it soothing.

21
00:04:43.604 --> 00:04:47.065
The message was damaged in transit
from Krypton to Earth.

22
00:04:47.066 --> 00:04:48.475
But what is there…

23
00:04:50.319 --> 00:04:52.646
"We love you
more than heaven. our son."

24
00:04:53.531 --> 00:04:54.906
"We love you more than land."

25
00:04:54.907 --> 00:04:56.491
"We love you more than land."

26
00:04:56.492 --> 00:04:59.202
"Our beloved home
will soon be gone forever.

27
00:04:59.203 --> 00:05:01.496
But hope vitalizes our hearts.

28
00:05:01.497 --> 00:05:03.824
and that hope is you. Kal-El."

29
00:05:05.459 --> 00:05:07.627
"We have searched
the universe for a home

30
00:05:07.628 --> 00:05:09.913
where you can do the most good

31
00:05:10.256 --> 00:05:12.708
and live out Krypton's truth.

32
00:05:13.592 --> 00:05:15.753
- That place is Earth.
- "That place is Earth."

33
00:05:16.262 --> 00:05:18.304
And the rest of the message is lost.

34
00:05:18.305 --> 00:05:20.014
Fourteen fractured bones.

35
00:05:20.015 --> 00:05:23.635
Damage to bladder. kidney.
large intestine. lungs.

36
00:05:24.061 --> 00:05:25.937
Our poor Superman.

37
00:05:25.938 --> 00:05:27.897
With a healthy dose of yellow sun.

38
00:05:27.898 --> 00:05:30.350
we'll have him up and at 'em in no time.

39
00:05:54.758 --> 00:05:56.176
Engineer. come in.

40
00:05:56.177 --> 00:05:58.344
He landed somewhere near here.

41
00:05:58.345 --> 00:05:59.797
I can't see where.

42
00:06:00.347 --> 00:06:01.924
Well. keep looking.

43
00:06:09.523 --> 00:06:12.267
Golly.

44
00:06:14.195 --> 00:06:18.198
Sir. you are only 83% restored
to health. You must rest.

45
00:06:18.199 --> 00:06:20.526
No can do. Four.
I gotta get back to the fray.

46
00:06:20.743 --> 00:06:24.037
But this Hammer fellow
just beat you at full power.

47
00:06:24.038 --> 00:06:25.406
Sir?

48
00:06:27.625 --> 00:06:29.326
What is this?

49
00:06:30.461 --> 00:06:31.495
Krypto!

50
00:06:33.422 --> 00:06:35.006
What the hey. dude?
I-I thought--

51
00:06:35.007 --> 00:06:36.417
You destroyed the whole--

52
00:06:36.617 --> 00:06:39.010
Superman robots. I thought I told you
to keep an eye on him.

53
00:06:39.011 --> 00:06:41.221
We feed the canine. but he is unruly.

54
00:06:41.222 --> 00:06:43.640
And he realizes
we are not flesh and blood

55
00:06:43.641 --> 00:06:47.302
and couldn't. in our heart of hearts.
care less whether he lives or dies.

56
00:06:47.895 --> 00:06:49.763
Stop. Krypto. leave it.

57
00:06:50.189 --> 00:06:52.815
Ow. Ow! Stop. Ow. Stop it.

58
00:06:52.816 --> 00:06:55.109
Krypto! Ow! Ow! Stop it. Stop.

59
00:06:55.110 --> 00:06:57.312
Sit. Sit. Stay.

60
00:07:13.337 --> 00:07:15.622
The alien is on its way back.

61
00:07:47.121 --> 00:07:50.032
Your Superman has abandoned you!

62
00:07:50.374 --> 00:07:55.788
The people of Boravia will not ignore him
inserting himself into our affairs.

63
00:08:00.301 --> 00:08:02.927
Accelerate the portals.

64
00:08:02.928 --> 00:08:04.470
Primed and ready.

65
00:08:04.471 --> 00:08:06.556
T-Minus ten and counting.

66
00:08:06.557 --> 00:08:07.807
Buckle up. we're going live.

67
00:08:07.808 --> 00:08:09.851
Ten. nine. eight. seven. six…

68
00:08:09.852 --> 00:08:11.352
Bravo. what do you have on employees?

69
00:08:11.353 --> 00:08:13.020
I'm inside Chocos. Larry. No fatalities.

70
00:08:13.021 --> 00:08:14.021
…five. four…

71
00:08:14.022 --> 00:08:17.092
- Can't win 'em all.
- …three. two. one.

72
00:08:18.527 --> 00:08:20.403
Target in sight.

73
00:08:20.404 --> 00:08:23.565
- He's back. Your 5:00.
- Copy.

74
00:08:28.829 --> 00:08:29.905
12C.

75
00:08:35.961 --> 00:08:37.037
18A.

76
00:08:42.175 --> 00:08:43.293
34B.

77
00:08:47.223 --> 00:08:48.298
98Z.

78
00:08:50.392 --> 00:08:51.392
8H.

79
00:08:54.271 --> 00:08:55.681
74D.

80
00:08:59.735 --> 00:09:01.228
44T!

81
00:09:11.622 --> 00:09:14.783
- Reggie. can you watch?
- Yeah. yeah.

82
00:09:17.044 --> 00:09:19.663
Yes! Yes. yes. yes!

83
00:09:20.589 --> 00:09:24.092
It's like he knows Superman's every move
before he makes it.

84
00:09:24.093 --> 00:09:26.970
He does. He's been studying him for years.

85
00:09:26.971 --> 00:09:30.223
He's developed over 2.500 fight moves
for any situation.

86
00:09:30.224 --> 00:09:32.509
Superman!

87
00:09:33.686 --> 00:09:35.387
Bravo. you got him?

88
00:09:36.939 --> 00:09:39.266
Malik Ali. a local.

89
00:09:39.567 --> 00:09:41.935
Lex. we have the Engineer.

90
00:09:43.362 --> 00:09:45.564
The target
has led us to the ice castle.

91
00:09:46.031 --> 00:09:47.448
The rumors are true.

92
00:09:47.449 --> 00:09:50.110
I don't know how in the hell
this thing hasn't been spotted.

93
00:09:56.625 --> 00:09:57.826
Mierda.

94
00:10:04.508 --> 00:10:06.043
Comms. two to one.

95
00:10:08.137 --> 00:10:09.588
Hijo de…

96
00:10:10.097 --> 00:10:13.342
Lex. the entire structure
has descended into the ice.

97
00:10:13.976 --> 00:10:15.727
We have what we need.
Return to base.

98
00:10:15.728 --> 00:10:17.520
I can drill into it. Lex.

99
00:10:17.521 --> 00:10:19.664
Your pride won't be making
our choices today. Angela.

100
00:10:19.665 --> 00:10:20.681
Thank you.

101
00:10:20.682 --> 00:10:22.509
We'll need more than you
when we enter.

102
00:10:24.069 --> 00:10:25.437
Comms. one to two.

103
00:10:26.155 --> 00:10:28.357
We've done what we need to do.
Wrap it up.

104
00:10:28.699 --> 00:10:34.279
The United States will continue to feel
the wrath of the Hammer of Boravia.

105
00:10:34.788 --> 00:10:35.906
It's me. Mali.

106
00:10:36.332 --> 00:10:37.991
Once I gave you free falafel.

107
00:10:38.292 --> 00:10:40.418
when you saved a woman
from being hit by a taxi.

108
00:10:40.419 --> 00:10:41.586
Are you all right. Superman?

109
00:10:41.587 --> 00:10:43.796
Mali. you gotta get outta here.
It's not safe.

110
00:10:43.797 --> 00:10:46.466
You saved us so many times.
Now it's our turn.

111
00:10:46.467 --> 00:10:48.711
This is your last warning.

112
00:10:49.220 --> 00:10:51.171
Oh!

113
00:10:54.308 --> 00:10:57.219
Maybe you shouldn't have done
that thing in Jarhanpur. Superman.

114
00:11:03.651 --> 00:11:05.235
Flawless. people.

115
00:11:05.236 --> 00:11:07.062
Way to bring it home!

116
00:12:00.374 --> 00:12:02.409
Decelerate all portals.

117
00:12:04.253 --> 00:12:05.795
- Ultraman's back.
- Ultraman!

118
00:12:05.796 --> 00:12:08.381
Ultraman! You did so good.

119
00:12:08.382 --> 00:12:09.958
Yes!

120
00:12:36.160 --> 00:12:37.653
Sorry about that. I'm so sorry.

121
00:12:38.662 --> 00:12:39.780
Sorry.

122
00:12:41.123 --> 00:12:42.825
- Morning. Nino.
- Good morning. Clark.

123
00:12:49.131 --> 00:12:51.341
Do these unelected metahumans

124
00:12:51.342 --> 00:12:54.010
think they can dictate
international policy?

125
00:12:54.011 --> 00:12:55.261
It's outrageous.

126
00:12:55.262 --> 00:12:57.847
It's a big story.
Put it above the fold.

127
00:12:57.848 --> 00:12:59.474
That's where we put it.

128
00:12:59.475 --> 00:13:02.136
- You're late again. Kent.
- Sorry. Perry.

129
00:13:02.603 --> 00:13:05.222
- Hey. loser.
- Hey. Steve.

130
00:13:05.481 --> 00:13:07.941
Hey. what do you got
against adverbs. Kent?

131
00:13:07.942 --> 00:13:11.311
How are we supposed to know how we feel
when we read this malarkey?

132
00:13:11.487 --> 00:13:15.649
In sports writing. you learn
the sentence is the modifier.

133
00:13:16.033 --> 00:13:17.651
- Hey. Ma.
- "Ma!"

134
00:13:17.993 --> 00:13:20.036
Hey. Clark!

135
00:13:20.037 --> 00:13:22.789
Uh. me and Pa just wanted to call

136
00:13:22.790 --> 00:13:26.376
and say congratulations
on that front page.

137
00:13:26.377 --> 00:13:28.378
Boy. that is something!

138
00:13:28.379 --> 00:13:30.880
Hey. ask Ma if she barbecued up
any good roadkill lately.

139
00:13:30.881 --> 00:13:33.424
- Shut up. Steve.
- Like. uh. possum or chitlins…

140
00:13:33.425 --> 00:13:35.009
- What's that. Clark?
- Sorry. Ma.

141
00:13:35.010 --> 00:13:36.835
I'm just in the middle
of a big news day here.

142
00:13:36.836 --> 00:13:37.920
What are chitlins?

143
00:13:37.921 --> 00:13:38.963
Chitlins are intestines.

144
00:13:38.964 --> 00:13:41.349
Thanks. Cat. You read this crud?

145
00:13:41.350 --> 00:13:43.052
I thought it was great. Clark.

146
00:13:43.686 --> 00:13:44.811
"Great"?

147
00:13:44.812 --> 00:13:47.021
Yeah! Front page! Big time!

148
00:13:47.022 --> 00:13:50.900
Well. we don't want
to keep you. but. uh.

149
00:13:50.901 --> 00:13:53.152
wanted to say congrats.

150
00:13:53.153 --> 00:13:55.947
and tell you we're thinking
'bout you. Clark.

151
00:13:55.948 --> 00:13:59.284
- It's been a minute.
- Tell him don't be a stranger.

152
00:13:59.285 --> 00:14:01.661
Pa says. "Don't be a stranger."

153
00:14:01.662 --> 00:14:03.663
I. uh… Yeah. I heard him. Ma.

154
00:14:03.664 --> 00:14:05.491
Yeah. okay I gotta go. I gotta run.

155
00:14:05.691 --> 00:14:06.708
Yep. okay. Love you.

156
00:14:06.709 --> 00:14:10.336
So. this guy just flew into midtown
and started attacking people.

157
00:14:10.337 --> 00:14:12.172
demanding for Superman to show up?

158
00:14:12.173 --> 00:14:14.215
Yeah. It's all there in my article.

159
00:14:14.216 --> 00:14:16.676
Then I'd actually have to make
it through your writing. Clark.

160
00:14:16.677 --> 00:14:18.686
Knowledge is worth many sacrifices.

161
00:14:18.687 --> 00:14:19.762
That isn't one of them.

162
00:14:19.763 --> 00:14:21.139
Ha. ha. ha. Very funny. Lois.

163
00:14:21.140 --> 00:14:23.099
- Oh. my God.
- He's so fine.

164
00:14:23.100 --> 00:14:26.144
Twenty-two people in the hospital.
over 20 million in property damage.

165
00:14:26.145 --> 00:14:28.188
- It does make you wonder.
- Wonder what?

166
00:14:28.189 --> 00:14:31.274
As great as he is. maybe Superman
didn't completely think through

167
00:14:31.275 --> 00:14:32.901
the ramifications of the Boravia thing.

168
00:14:32.902 --> 00:14:35.153
If this guy is even from Boravia.

169
00:14:35.154 --> 00:14:37.405
What do you mean?
His name is "the Hammer of Boravia."

170
00:14:37.406 --> 00:14:39.824
Yeah. I doubt his parents
named him that. Jimmy.

171
00:14:39.825 --> 00:14:41.893
We have no clue
what his actual goal was here.

172
00:14:41.894 --> 00:14:44.454
I think it's pretty obvious the
goal was kicking Superman's ass.

173
00:14:44.455 --> 00:14:46.598
Uh. he did-- He didn't
completely kick Superman's ass.

174
00:14:46.599 --> 00:14:47.640
Pretty thoroughly. Clark.

175
00:14:47.641 --> 00:14:51.419
Show me! You show me
what ties there are

176
00:14:51.420 --> 00:14:54.506
between Boravia and this "Hammer!"

177
00:14:54.507 --> 00:14:56.841
Yeah. see. Superman did say
he thought the. uh. Hammer

178
00:14:56.842 --> 00:14:58.544
might be faking a Boravian accent.

179
00:14:58.802 --> 00:14:59.886
Superman said that?

180
00:14:59.887 --> 00:15:02.089
Yeah. I interviewed him
right afterwards. Great guy.

181
00:15:02.389 --> 00:15:06.142
You know. it's funny that you keep getting
all these interviews with Superman. Clark.

182
00:15:06.143 --> 00:15:09.054
I don't think there's anything funny
about good journalism. Lois.

183
00:15:09.230 --> 00:15:10.355
Uh-huh.

184
00:15:10.356 --> 00:15:15.485
The relationship
between Boravia and United States

185
00:15:15.486 --> 00:15:19.606
has been like iron for 30 years.

186
00:15:19.782 --> 00:15:23.152
until Superman came along.

187
00:15:25.412 --> 00:15:27.121
What you're looking at.
my friends.

188
00:15:27.122 --> 00:15:30.993
is the most powerful being
on Planet Earth:

189
00:15:31.669 --> 00:15:33.370
Ultraman.

190
00:15:33.796 --> 00:15:35.255
You created this man?

191
00:15:35.256 --> 00:15:38.424
Ooh. Check this out. The Engineer.

192
00:15:38.425 --> 00:15:41.052
A former special operative.
whose blood I infused

193
00:15:41.053 --> 00:15:43.672
with microscopic machines
called "nanites."

194
00:15:43.764 --> 00:15:47.426
which she can form into anything
she can imagine.

195
00:15:47.685 --> 00:15:52.105
And. of course. you're familiar with
my flying armored forces. the Raptors.

196
00:15:52.106 --> 00:15:57.186
All together. they're an unstoppable force
we call PlanetWatch.

197
00:15:58.404 --> 00:16:02.024
More than capable of containing
any otherworldly threat.

198
00:16:04.285 --> 00:16:06.536
So you want the Defense Department

199
00:16:06.537 --> 00:16:10.123
to hire your metahumans
to take down the Kryptonian?

200
00:16:10.124 --> 00:16:13.793
After Superman acted with violence
against our Boravian allies.

201
00:16:13.794 --> 00:16:15.219
I think it'd be worth considering.

202
00:16:15.220 --> 00:16:16.880
Big Blue stopped a war.

203
00:16:16.881 --> 00:16:18.673
Naive. maybe. but well-intentioned.

204
00:16:18.674 --> 00:16:23.178
Well. I don't know the intentions
of an unattended firehose. General Flag.

205
00:16:23.179 --> 00:16:25.597
I just do what I can not to be splashed.

206
00:16:25.598 --> 00:16:28.558
- Mr. Luthor…
- The disarming Director Crawley.

207
00:16:28.559 --> 00:16:30.643
The country
of Boravia has purchased

208
00:16:30.644 --> 00:16:32.896
over 80 billion dollars' worth of arms

209
00:16:32.897 --> 00:16:35.182
from LuthorCorp in the past two years.

210
00:16:35.274 --> 00:16:36.858
- And?
- And no one would profit more

211
00:16:36.859 --> 00:16:39.652
from a war with Boravia
and Jarhanpur than you.

212
00:16:39.653 --> 00:16:42.071
A cynic might say that having
Superman out of the way

213
00:16:42.072 --> 00:16:43.406
might not be bad for business.

214
00:16:43.407 --> 00:16:46.527
Well. what's particularly
bad for business is dying.

215
00:16:46.619 --> 00:16:49.537
And I have a distinct feeling
that's where we're all headed

216
00:16:49.538 --> 00:16:51.080
with the Kryptonian running wild.

217
00:16:51.081 --> 00:16:53.416
So we're gonna lock up all metahumans now?

218
00:16:53.417 --> 00:16:55.877
Look. other metahumans
aren't going off half-cocked.

219
00:16:55.878 --> 00:16:57.670
interfering in foreign affairs.

220
00:16:57.671 --> 00:17:00.006
They don't have--
And I have proof of this--

221
00:17:00.007 --> 00:17:02.592
a hidden headquarters in Antarctica

222
00:17:02.593 --> 00:17:05.344
that violates 12 international treaties.

223
00:17:05.345 --> 00:17:08.515
And they aren't aliens.

224
00:17:08.516 --> 00:17:11.267
Shouldn't all that be
more than enough reason

225
00:17:11.268 --> 00:17:15.979
for PlanetWatch to at least bring
the Kryptonian in for questioning?

226
00:17:15.980 --> 00:17:18.107
Admittedly. I'm not comfortable

227
00:17:18.108 --> 00:17:22.070
with a being from another planet
as dangerous as him on the loose.

228
00:17:22.071 --> 00:17:24.572
But the optics? Superman is popular.

229
00:17:24.573 --> 00:17:27.116
Less so every day.
according to chatter online.

230
00:17:27.117 --> 00:17:30.078
Not to mention the potential risk
of failing to contain him.

231
00:17:30.079 --> 00:17:32.539
I assure you. Secretary.
we can contain him.

232
00:17:32.540 --> 00:17:34.649
Yeah. they got this stuff. uh…

233
00:17:34.650 --> 00:17:36.125
What's this
Kryptonite stuff called?

234
00:17:36.126 --> 00:17:38.920
- It's called Kryptonite.
- Well. it kills him. right?

235
00:17:38.921 --> 00:17:41.347
As far as we can ascertain.
there's none left on the planet.

236
00:17:41.348 --> 00:17:42.982
I have a workaround for that as well.

237
00:17:42.983 --> 00:17:44.634
You know what? It doesn't matter. Lex.

238
00:17:44.635 --> 00:17:46.678
Because without solid proof
of malicious intent.

239
00:17:46.679 --> 00:17:48.172
it's just not worth the risk.

240
00:18:27.344 --> 00:18:29.012
What are you doing here?

241
00:18:29.013 --> 00:18:30.805
Three months ago. we had our first date.

242
00:18:30.806 --> 00:18:34.642
And so. to celebrate.
I am making you your favorite:

243
00:18:34.643 --> 00:18:36.144
breakfast for dinner.

244
00:18:36.145 --> 00:18:37.679
That's your favorite.

245
00:18:38.022 --> 00:18:39.189
You love breakfast.

246
00:18:39.190 --> 00:18:42.142
Yeah. for breakfast.
You love it for dinner.

247
00:19:01.362 --> 00:19:03.179
- What?
- It was very funny today.

248
00:19:03.180 --> 00:19:04.264
- What?
- It was hilarious.

249
00:19:04.265 --> 00:19:05.882
the little back-and-forth we had going.

250
00:19:05.883 --> 00:19:06.933
Mm.

251
00:19:06.934 --> 00:19:08.760
You giving me guff for my article.

252
00:19:08.761 --> 00:19:10.512
Jimmy was eating it up.

253
00:19:10.513 --> 00:19:14.015
I wasn't acting. Clark.
If you keep interviewing yourself.

254
00:19:14.016 --> 00:19:16.643
eventually people
are gonna figure it out.

255
00:19:16.644 --> 00:19:18.061
But the glasses.

256
00:19:18.062 --> 00:19:20.647
Yeah. they won't fool everyone forever.

257
00:19:20.648 --> 00:19:25.276
And ethically. these interviews
are hugely problematic.

258
00:19:25.277 --> 00:19:28.397
I mean. y-you literally know
the questions in advance.

259
00:19:29.156 --> 00:19:30.691
Okay. so I'll let you interview me.

260
00:19:31.116 --> 00:19:32.909
I'm pretty sure
you wouldn't like that.

261
00:19:32.910 --> 00:19:34.911
Come on. Lois. I'm media savvy.

262
00:19:34.912 --> 00:19:38.498
I can handle any question
that comes my way.

263
00:19:38.499 --> 00:19:40.325
Are you being serious right now?

264
00:19:40.918 --> 00:19:41.994
Yeah.

265
00:19:42.503 --> 00:19:44.872
You'd let me interview you as Superman?

266
00:19:46.340 --> 00:19:47.541
Sure.

267
00:19:48.759 --> 00:19:49.960
How about now?

268
00:19:52.888 --> 00:19:54.048
Um…

269
00:19:56.517 --> 00:19:57.517
Ready?

270
00:19:57.726 --> 00:19:59.386
Let's do it. Cronkite.

271
00:20:00.145 --> 00:20:01.430
Superman.

272
00:20:02.231 --> 00:20:03.474
Miss Lane.

273
00:20:03.949 --> 00:20:05.041
Recently. you've come under

274
00:20:05.042 --> 00:20:06.526
a lot of fire for what some might--

275
00:20:06.527 --> 00:20:08.127
I don't know
if it's a lot of fire. but--

276
00:20:08.128 --> 00:20:09.162
It's a lot.

277
00:20:09.163 --> 00:20:10.438
Today the Secretary of Defense

278
00:20:10.439 --> 00:20:12.674
said he was gonna look into
your actions in Boravia.

279
00:20:12.675 --> 00:20:14.784
That-- That's funny?

280
00:20:14.785 --> 00:20:17.704
It's not "funny" funny. it's just. um…

281
00:20:17.705 --> 00:20:20.449
I mean. come on. My actions?
I stopped a war.

282
00:20:20.833 --> 00:20:22.959
- Maybe.
- Uh. not "maybe." I did.

283
00:20:22.960 --> 00:20:24.919
Okay. How?

284
00:20:24.920 --> 00:20:27.755
Well. Boravia invaded Jarhanpur.

285
00:20:27.756 --> 00:20:30.008
and I showed up and told them
that wasn't right.

286
00:20:30.009 --> 00:20:31.058
And?

287
00:20:31.059 --> 00:20:33.094
And… smashed some tanks and things

288
00:20:33.095 --> 00:20:36.173
and a couple of planes
and some other stuff.

289
00:20:37.057 --> 00:20:39.517
There were no casualties
and no significant injuries.

290
00:20:39.518 --> 00:20:40.643
Did you interact at all

291
00:20:40.644 --> 00:20:43.222
with the President of Boravia.
Vasil Ghurkos?

292
00:20:43.397 --> 00:20:44.480
A very small amount.

293
00:20:44.481 --> 00:20:46.100
What's a very small amount?

294
00:20:46.775 --> 00:20:48.018
That was between us.

295
00:20:50.863 --> 00:20:52.113
This is all on the record.

296
00:20:52.114 --> 00:20:55.617
Yeah. but that conversation
was between the two of us.

297
00:20:55.618 --> 00:20:57.577
Yeah. and I would
ask that question

298
00:20:57.578 --> 00:20:59.329
whether or not
I knew the answer to it.

299
00:20:59.330 --> 00:21:00.948
- Really?
- Really.

300
00:21:02.500 --> 00:21:04.576
After I stopped the war.

301
00:21:05.211 --> 00:21:06.503
I went to see Ghurkos.

302
00:21:06.504 --> 00:21:07.587
Where?

303
00:21:07.588 --> 00:21:09.614
In the capital of Luchebic.
at the Royal Palace.

304
00:21:09.615 --> 00:21:10.665
And?

305
00:21:10.666 --> 00:21:12.717
And I took a private audience
with Ghurkos.

306
00:21:12.718 --> 00:21:13.793
How?

307
00:21:13.794 --> 00:21:16.538
I flew him out to the desert. and I…

308
00:21:16.805 --> 00:21:18.056
And you…

309
00:21:18.057 --> 00:21:20.217
And I placed him
against a cactus.

310
00:21:20.392 --> 00:21:21.809
A cactus?

311
00:21:21.810 --> 00:21:23.795
So… torture?

312
00:21:23.796 --> 00:21:24.854
No. Not torture.

313
00:21:24.855 --> 00:21:27.099
Its spikes were like…
not even that big.

314
00:21:27.191 --> 00:21:28.274
What did you say?

315
00:21:28.275 --> 00:21:31.194
I told him that if he ever
messes with Jarhanpur again.

316
00:21:31.195 --> 00:21:32.862
he'll have to
personally answer to me.

317
00:21:32.863 --> 00:21:34.364
What did you mean by that?

318
00:21:34.365 --> 00:21:35.907
That if such events occurred.

319
00:21:35.908 --> 00:21:38.493
we would have a more serious
discussion. that's all.

320
00:21:38.494 --> 00:21:41.037
More serious than
tearing up his back on a cactus?

321
00:21:41.038 --> 00:21:42.247
Ghurkos was gonna kill people.

322
00:21:42.248 --> 00:21:43.623
You seem to keep
forgetting that--

323
00:21:43.624 --> 00:21:45.809
So. in effect.
you illegally entered a country.

324
00:21:45.810 --> 00:21:47.127
inserting yourself in the middle

325
00:21:47.128 --> 00:21:49.120
- of an incredibly heated…
- No. no. no. Hold on.

326
00:21:49.121 --> 00:21:50.904
- geopolitical situation…
- Hold on a second.

327
00:21:50.905 --> 00:21:53.491
…siding with a nation. Jarhanpur.
which historically has not been

328
00:21:53.492 --> 00:21:55.292
- a friend to the US…
- Jarhanpur has changed.

329
00:21:55.293 --> 00:21:57.093
…against a nation
that's technically our ally.

330
00:21:57.094 --> 00:21:59.145
and then threatened
to murder their head of state.

331
00:21:59.146 --> 00:22:01.586
First of all. whether or not
Jarhanpur is an imperfect country

332
00:22:01.587 --> 00:22:03.627
does not give another nation
the right to invade it.

333
00:22:03.628 --> 00:22:05.268
Yes. but the Boravian government
maintains

334
00:22:05.269 --> 00:22:07.589
they're freeing the Jarhanpurians
from a tyrannical regime.

335
00:22:07.590 --> 00:22:09.190
Yes. but you know that's very silly.

336
00:22:09.191 --> 00:22:10.208
I do?

337
00:22:10.209 --> 00:22:13.278
The Boravian government.
of all people. is saying this?

338
00:22:13.279 --> 00:22:14.370
Come on!

339
00:22:14.371 --> 00:22:15.880
This is on the record. Superman.

340
00:22:15.881 --> 00:22:17.198
Now-- No. Now. see…

341
00:22:17.199 --> 00:22:18.658
Now you're being
dishonest. Lois.

342
00:22:18.659 --> 00:22:20.611
How am I being dishonest?

343
00:22:21.504 --> 00:22:23.271
- What are you--? Stop.
- Where's the button?

344
00:22:23.272 --> 00:22:25.498
You're being dishonest
because you know as well as I do

345
00:22:25.499 --> 00:22:27.641
that the Boravian government
is not well-intentioned.

346
00:22:27.642 --> 00:22:30.703
I think that's almost certainly
the case. but do I know that?

347
00:22:30.704 --> 00:22:31.863
No. I don't.

348
00:22:32.882 --> 00:22:34.208
Can we go on now?

349
00:22:34.675 --> 00:22:35.800
Yeah. fine.

350
00:22:35.801 --> 00:22:37.169
- I don't-- You do it.
- I…

351
00:22:39.638 --> 00:22:40.923
You think this is going well?

352
00:22:41.015 --> 00:22:43.384
Do I think this is going well?
Um…

353
00:22:44.185 --> 00:22:45.803
I think I'm doing a good job.

354
00:22:48.397 --> 00:22:50.148
Superman. did you consult
with the President

355
00:22:50.149 --> 00:22:51.683
before entering
Boravian airspace?

356
00:22:53.485 --> 00:22:54.819
- No.
- The Secretary of Defense?

357
00:22:54.820 --> 00:22:56.554
- No.
- Or any US official

358
00:22:56.555 --> 00:22:58.348
before you took matters
into your own hands

359
00:22:58.349 --> 00:23:00.025
and decided unilaterally
how to handle

360
00:23:00.026 --> 00:23:01.409
this extremely delicate
situation?

361
00:23:01.410 --> 00:23:04.120
Ghurkos and his goons
were going to kill people.

362
00:23:04.121 --> 00:23:05.497
Yes. but the results

363
00:23:05.498 --> 00:23:07.407
of you seemingly acting
as a representative

364
00:23:07.408 --> 00:23:08.708
of the United States
will cause…

365
00:23:08.709 --> 00:23:09.909
I wasn't representing
anybody…

366
00:23:09.910 --> 00:23:10.902
…more problems
around the world.

367
00:23:10.903 --> 00:23:11.836
…except for me. and-and…

368
00:23:11.837 --> 00:23:13.638
- More than a war that lasted…
- …myself and. and. and…

369
00:23:13.639 --> 00:23:14.614
…between 12 and 24 hours…

370
00:23:14.615 --> 00:23:15.573
…good. I don't know.
doing good.

371
00:23:15.574 --> 00:23:16.591
…and was just replacing

372
00:23:16.592 --> 00:23:18.092
one tyrannical regime
with another?

373
00:23:18.093 --> 00:23:19.469
Is that really how you feel?

374
00:23:19.470 --> 00:23:22.798
I'm not the one being
interviewed. Superman. but…

375
00:23:23.390 --> 00:23:25.058
I question it.

376
00:23:25.059 --> 00:23:27.810
Yeah. I would question myself
in the same situation

377
00:23:27.811 --> 00:23:30.522
and hold off a beat
and consider the consequences.

378
00:23:30.523 --> 00:23:32.725
People were going to die!

379
00:23:42.618 --> 00:23:45.571
Okay. I'd like to
change the subject. if I could.

380
00:23:46.163 --> 00:23:47.330
Okay.

381
00:23:47.331 --> 00:23:49.541
You've gotten a lot of heat
on social media lately.

382
00:23:49.542 --> 00:23:50.667
I don't read that stuff.

383
00:23:50.668 --> 00:23:52.953
Superman doesn't have
time for selfies.

384
00:23:53.871 --> 00:23:55.205
- Third person?
- Hmm?

385
00:23:55.206 --> 00:23:57.349
You're referring to yourself
in the third person now?

386
00:23:57.350 --> 00:23:58.842
No. it was just a thing
I came up with

387
00:23:58.843 --> 00:24:01.085
that I thought I'd try to work
into the next interview.

388
00:24:01.086 --> 00:24:02.420
This is on the record. Superman.

389
00:24:02.421 --> 00:24:04.147
Okay. well. not the part
where I said that.

390
00:24:04.148 --> 00:24:06.391
- Yes. that part.
- No. that part was an aside.

391
00:24:06.392 --> 00:24:07.392
That was off the record.

392
00:24:07.393 --> 00:24:10.228
You have to say "off the record"
beforehand. not after.

393
00:24:10.229 --> 00:24:11.771
Why are you being like this?

394
00:24:11.772 --> 00:24:13.106
Fine. I-I won't write

395
00:24:13.107 --> 00:24:15.567
that you spend your spare time
trying to think up soundbites.

396
00:24:15.568 --> 00:24:17.061
Which are terrible. by the way.

397
00:24:17.511 --> 00:24:19.179
- Social media.
- Yes.

398
00:24:19.180 --> 00:24:21.347
As you may know.
or maybe you don't.

399
00:24:21.348 --> 00:24:23.283
since you claim not to read
any of that stuff--

400
00:24:23.284 --> 00:24:24.359
Very seldomly.

401
00:24:24.360 --> 00:24:26.110
Maybe sometimes people
catch you reading it

402
00:24:26.111 --> 00:24:27.537
and looking very upset.

403
00:24:27.538 --> 00:24:29.205
Okay. well. you can't use that.

404
00:24:29.206 --> 00:24:32.451
People on social media are
suspicious because you are…

405
00:24:32.960 --> 00:24:34.544
…an alien. yes?

406
00:24:34.545 --> 00:24:35.628
Yes.

407
00:24:35.629 --> 00:24:38.332
I've been very honest
about that. From the beginning.

408
00:24:38.799 --> 00:24:40.709
I come from
a planet called Krypton.

409
00:24:40.843 --> 00:24:43.219
- Okay.
- Which is gone now. by the way.

410
00:24:43.220 --> 00:24:45.923
Destroyed.
Along with all of my history.

411
00:24:46.390 --> 00:24:47.640
My parents.

412
00:24:47.641 --> 00:24:49.559
They sent me here as a baby
to save my life.

413
00:24:49.560 --> 00:24:50.685
Here. where?

414
00:24:50.686 --> 00:24:52.971
I'm not gonna say that.
You know I'm not gonna say that.

415
00:24:55.441 --> 00:24:56.517
Okay.

416
00:24:59.570 --> 00:25:02.898
What do you know about these
biological parents of yours?

417
00:25:03.032 --> 00:25:06.652
Just that they sent me here
to serve humanity

418
00:25:07.411 --> 00:25:10.038
and to help the world
to be a better place.

419
00:25:10.039 --> 00:25:12.282
- They said that?
- They did.

420
00:25:13.292 --> 00:25:15.536
They sent a message
along with me.

421
00:25:17.922 --> 00:25:20.131
That message
is why I do what I do.

422
00:25:20.132 --> 00:25:22.042
I cherish it more than anything.

423
00:25:22.718 --> 00:25:24.677
Because you understand now.

424
00:25:24.678 --> 00:25:26.888
there are an awful lot of people
out there maintaining

425
00:25:26.889 --> 00:25:30.141
you're here
for more nefarious purposes.

426
00:25:30.142 --> 00:25:32.469
Hashtag Superspy.
Hashtag Supershit.

427
00:25:32.686 --> 00:25:34.020
Supershit!? Come on. Lois!

428
00:25:34.021 --> 00:25:35.788
You know that one
specifically irritates me!

429
00:25:35.789 --> 00:25:37.941
This is on the record. Clark!

430
00:25:37.942 --> 00:25:38.942
I didn't make it up.

431
00:25:38.943 --> 00:25:41.145
It's what people on the Internet
are saying.

432
00:25:41.403 --> 00:25:42.737
I'm gonna go.

433
00:25:42.738 --> 00:25:44.656
- Really?
- Yeah.

434
00:25:44.657 --> 00:25:46.658
Come on. Clark. Don't do this.

435
00:25:46.659 --> 00:25:47.867
I'm not doing anything.

436
00:25:47.868 --> 00:25:49.669
No? No. that's not you.
packing up your shit

437
00:25:49.670 --> 00:25:51.206
and walking out of an interview?

438
00:25:51.207 --> 00:25:53.489
I'm not walking out of an interview.
I'm just-- It's late.

439
00:25:53.490 --> 00:25:55.483
No. this is what you do every time
you're faced with conflict.

440
00:25:55.484 --> 00:25:57.076
- I'm not doing anything.
- You get mad. You pout.

441
00:25:57.077 --> 00:25:58.244
- Then you pretend…
- I'm not mad.

442
00:25:58.245 --> 00:25:59.528
- …like nothing's wrong.
- Nothing is wrong.

443
00:25:59.529 --> 00:26:01.414
Look. I gave you
a nice. long interview.

444
00:26:01.415 --> 00:26:03.508
Longer than I ever gave myself.
by the way.

445
00:26:03.509 --> 00:26:06.094
Oh. you can time your imaginary
interviews with yourself?

446
00:26:06.095 --> 00:26:07.220
That's a thing you can do?

447
00:26:07.221 --> 00:26:08.672
You got a lot of good stuff.

448
00:26:09.557 --> 00:26:10.890
Some stuff you can't use.

449
00:26:10.891 --> 00:26:12.843
I am well aware.

450
00:26:13.644 --> 00:26:15.262
I knew this would never work.

451
00:26:16.605 --> 00:26:17.890
What does that mean?

452
00:26:21.110 --> 00:26:22.227
Lois?

453
00:26:23.821 --> 00:26:25.981
- What does that mean?
- Nothing. I just…

454
00:26:26.282 --> 00:26:28.734
I told you
I wasn't good at relationships.

455
00:26:33.205 --> 00:26:34.365
Okay.

456
00:27:04.528 --> 00:27:07.071
The real Antarctica!

457
00:27:07.072 --> 00:27:08.857
So cool!

458
00:27:15.998 --> 00:27:17.408
It was right ahead.

459
00:27:17.875 --> 00:27:19.743
But how are we going to gain access?

460
00:27:20.461 --> 00:27:22.746
Oh. ye of little faith.

461
00:27:28.677 --> 00:27:30.629
Oh. wow!

462
00:27:43.651 --> 00:27:45.728
Oh. my God!

463
00:27:59.250 --> 00:28:01.994
Superman. I preemptively
put up the soothing--

464
00:28:02.419 --> 00:28:05.706
Oh. my. I do apologize.
but this is a restricted area.

465
00:28:07.299 --> 00:28:09.251
Wait. Can we talk--

466
00:29:10.196 --> 00:29:11.772
This is what we came for.

467
00:29:12.873 --> 00:29:14.282
Hopefully.
there's something on here

468
00:29:14.283 --> 00:29:15.742
we can use
to convince the general

469
00:29:15.743 --> 00:29:18.362
Superman requires immediate action.

470
00:29:18.871 --> 00:29:22.032
I can't stand the metahumans.
but he's so much worse.

471
00:29:22.708 --> 00:29:24.868
Super… man.

472
00:29:25.920 --> 00:29:27.871
He's not a man. He's an it.

473
00:29:28.506 --> 00:29:31.007
A thing with a cocky grin
and a stupid outfit

474
00:29:31.008 --> 00:29:32.500
that's somehow become the focal point

475
00:29:32.501 --> 00:29:34.645
of the entire world's conversation.

476
00:29:35.930 --> 00:29:37.923
Nothing's felt right
since he showed up.

477
00:29:38.724 --> 00:29:40.350
I know. Lex.

478
00:29:40.351 --> 00:29:44.096
I've sacrificed my own humanity
to help get rid of it.

479
00:29:44.563 --> 00:29:45.806
Can you get in?

480
00:29:51.070 --> 00:29:52.438
Might take a while.

481
00:29:52.696 --> 00:29:54.113
What if the Kryptonian shows up?

482
00:29:54.114 --> 00:29:55.315
Don't worry.

483
00:29:55.449 --> 00:29:58.235
I'm creating a… distraction.

484
00:30:38.826 --> 00:30:41.070
What?

485
00:30:41.287 --> 00:30:42.613
This message…

486
00:30:43.038 --> 00:30:44.782
…from his parents.

487
00:30:45.499 --> 00:30:47.167
It's damaged. but there's more.

488
00:30:47.168 --> 00:30:49.119
It's…

489
00:30:49.712 --> 00:30:51.163
I can recover the rest.

490
00:31:12.568 --> 00:31:14.569
Whoa! Got it!

491
00:31:14.570 --> 00:31:15.854
Let it out!

492
00:31:25.289 --> 00:31:27.616
It's an awfully small distraction.

493
00:31:27.917 --> 00:31:29.326
It'll get bigger.

494
00:31:46.227 --> 00:31:47.678
Get! Go!

495
00:31:52.441 --> 00:31:54.268
Get! Get outta here!

496
00:32:42.158 --> 00:32:43.283
The giant animal

497
00:32:43.284 --> 00:32:45.034
was first spotted early this morning

498
00:32:45.035 --> 00:32:48.121
in a Jitters coffee shop
about seven feet tall.

499
00:32:48.122 --> 00:32:50.157
but it has apparently been growing.

500
00:33:00.217 --> 00:33:02.544
Everybody okay?

501
00:33:05.973 --> 00:33:08.258
Hey. buddy. Eyes up here.

502
00:33:46.805 --> 00:33:49.633
Deep. slow breaths. ma'am.
You're gonna be fine.

503
00:34:02.571 --> 00:34:05.149
Everybody. clear the area.

504
00:34:06.992 --> 00:34:09.368
He's just so cheap. like. so obnoxious.

505
00:34:09.369 --> 00:34:10.738
You know what I mean?

506
00:34:11.914 --> 00:34:13.790
You can afford
$1.000 concert tickets…

507
00:34:13.791 --> 00:34:16.175
Finally a bit of good news
amid the chaos here this morning.

508
00:34:16.176 --> 00:34:18.895
The Justice Gang
has arrived on the scene.

509
00:34:18.896 --> 00:34:22.006
That's Green Lantern. Hawkgirl
and Mr. Terrific.

510
00:34:22.007 --> 00:34:24.209
They're funded
by the LordTech corporation.

511
00:34:24.385 --> 00:34:25.502
Get him!

512
00:34:31.642 --> 00:34:32.676
Hey!

513
00:34:59.211 --> 00:35:00.829
Heel. boy!

514
00:35:10.264 --> 00:35:11.890
- What's the skinny?
- Its hide is tough.

515
00:35:11.891 --> 00:35:13.808
but. uh. it's off balance.

516
00:35:13.809 --> 00:35:16.436
I've been trying to figure out a way
to get it out of here alive.

517
00:35:16.467 --> 00:35:18.284
Get it someplace
where we can study it.

518
00:35:18.285 --> 00:35:20.885
- Oh. come on. man.
- What?

519
00:35:20.886 --> 00:35:23.418
Go for its eyes!

520
00:35:39.919 --> 00:35:43.296
My knee! Guy. help!

521
00:35:43.297 --> 00:35:45.124
I made giant oven mitts!

522
00:35:45.466 --> 00:35:47.918
Good for you. asshole!
I'm getting blinked to death!

523
00:36:03.400 --> 00:36:04.935
Come on. be careful!

524
00:36:12.952 --> 00:36:14.494
Oh!

525
00:36:14.495 --> 00:36:16.947
Good gosh! There's gotta be
a better way to do this.

526
00:36:42.648 --> 00:36:44.308
Come on.

527
00:37:03.544 --> 00:37:05.295
Authorities are
saying there haven't been

528
00:37:05.296 --> 00:37:06.963
any signs yet of loss of life.

529
00:37:06.964 --> 00:37:09.465
thanks to Metropolis
hometown hero. Superman.

530
00:37:09.466 --> 00:37:12.093
but the damage to property
could be in the millions.

531
00:37:12.094 --> 00:37:13.111
City spokespeople…

532
00:37:13.112 --> 00:37:15.763
How's it going with that guy
you were seeing?

533
00:37:15.764 --> 00:37:18.175
You were saying
you weren't sure about it?

534
00:37:18.851 --> 00:37:20.719
Yeah. He's…

535
00:37:21.270 --> 00:37:23.263
a little strange.

536
00:37:29.612 --> 00:37:33.281
Ooh!
Kaiju steaks all around. huh?

537
00:37:33.282 --> 00:37:34.949
I was hoping we could capture it

538
00:37:34.950 --> 00:37:37.111
and take it
to an intergalactic zoo or…

539
00:37:38.162 --> 00:37:40.079
…at least euthanize it
less painfully.

540
00:37:40.080 --> 00:37:42.116
Come on. bro.
Don't be such a wuss.

541
00:37:42.500 --> 00:37:45.668
'Ey! Just another day in
the life of the Justice Gang!

542
00:37:45.669 --> 00:37:46.794
Not our name.

543
00:37:46.795 --> 00:37:47.904
It's just a working name.

544
00:37:47.905 --> 00:37:49.714
Could very well prove
to be permanent though.

545
00:37:49.715 --> 00:37:51.925
- Probably not!
- Good chance though. I'm saying.

546
00:37:51.926 --> 00:37:53.426
You okay? Everybody okay?

547
00:37:53.427 --> 00:37:54.594
Just like to say thank you

548
00:37:54.595 --> 00:37:57.631
on behalf of LordTech Industries
for the opportunity--

549
00:37:59.475 --> 00:38:00.926
Why is nobody clapping?

550
00:38:08.651 --> 00:38:09.852
Come here.

551
00:38:10.736 --> 00:38:12.604
This has to be BS.

552
00:38:14.582 --> 00:38:15.999
Well. they couldn't be mistaken?

553
00:38:16.000 --> 00:38:17.050
Oh. no.

554
00:38:17.051 --> 00:38:19.452
Well. that sounds very disturbing. Lex.

555
00:38:19.453 --> 00:38:21.137
Twenty-eight
of the world's top linguists

556
00:38:21.138 --> 00:38:23.373
have confirmed the translation

557
00:38:23.374 --> 00:38:25.542
and 30 of the top forensic
computer techs

558
00:38:25.543 --> 00:38:28.628
have confirmed the validity
of the footage itself.

559
00:38:28.629 --> 00:38:30.213
Any chance they're mistaken?

560
00:38:30.214 --> 00:38:32.833
Unfortunately. no.

561
00:38:33.300 --> 00:38:34.717
- You have the footage?
- Yes.

562
00:38:34.718 --> 00:38:35.794
Let's take a look.

563
00:38:37.721 --> 00:38:40.223
We love you
more than heaven. our son.

564
00:38:40.224 --> 00:38:41.925
We love you more than land.

565
00:38:42.601 --> 00:38:46.055
Our beloved home
is soon to be gone forever.

566
00:38:46.689 --> 00:38:48.523
But hope vitalizes our hearts.

567
00:38:48.524 --> 00:38:51.101
and that hope is you. Kal-El.

568
00:38:52.653 --> 00:38:53.862
We have searched the universe

569
00:38:53.863 --> 00:38:55.981
for a home where you can do the most good.

570
00:38:56.574 --> 00:38:58.700
And live out Krypton's truth.

571
00:38:58.701 --> 00:39:00.160
That place is Earth.

572
00:39:00.161 --> 00:39:01.737
I don't get it. What's bad about that?

573
00:39:05.082 --> 00:39:07.167
The people there are simple

574
00:39:07.168 --> 00:39:09.244
and profoundly confused.

575
00:39:10.421 --> 00:39:13.207
Weak of mind
and spirit and body.

576
00:39:14.675 --> 00:39:16.217
Lord over the planet

577
00:39:16.218 --> 00:39:18.045
as the last son of Krypton.

578
00:39:20.222 --> 00:39:21.347
Dispatch of anyone

579
00:39:21.348 --> 00:39:24.009
unable or unwilling to serve you. Kal-EI.

580
00:39:25.561 --> 00:39:27.979
Take as many wives as you can.

581
00:39:27.980 --> 00:39:31.107
so your genes and Krypton's
might and legacy

582
00:39:31.108 --> 00:39:33.185
will live on
in this new frontier.

583
00:39:35.446 --> 00:39:37.572
Do us proud. our beloved son.

584
00:39:37.573 --> 00:39:39.566
Rule without mercy.

585
00:39:41.577 --> 00:39:42.885
But what about all the kind acts

586
00:39:42.886 --> 00:39:44.787
Superman has performed
over the years.

587
00:39:44.788 --> 00:39:46.706
saving countless lives?

588
00:39:46.707 --> 00:39:50.035
No. He's grooming us.

589
00:39:50.294 --> 00:39:52.420
Lulling us into complacency.

590
00:39:52.421 --> 00:39:55.131
so he can dominate without resistance.

591
00:39:55.132 --> 00:39:56.758
forging a path for his

592
00:39:56.759 --> 00:39:59.378
super-powered descendants
to rule the Earth.

593
00:40:00.221 --> 00:40:05.926
I will not accept that. Will you?

594
00:40:08.771 --> 00:40:11.598
- You seem upset.
- I'm…

595
00:40:13.275 --> 00:40:14.351
I'm scared.

596
00:40:14.693 --> 00:40:16.895
I will admit that. I am scared.

597
00:40:17.196 --> 00:40:23.318
Because who knows how large
his secret harem is already?

598
00:40:44.473 --> 00:40:48.802
Oh. hell no!
Let me in! I'm serious!

599
00:40:53.607 --> 00:40:55.233
Dude. you got a secret harem?

600
00:40:55.234 --> 00:40:56.876
No. Guy. of course
I don't have a harem.

601
00:40:56.877 --> 00:40:59.654
If any of that message
is even remotely true.

602
00:40:59.655 --> 00:41:02.574
then you are exactly
the kind of alien threat

603
00:41:02.575 --> 00:41:04.868
I was commandeered
by the Green Lantern Corps

604
00:41:04.869 --> 00:41:06.452
to protect this planet against.

605
00:41:06.453 --> 00:41:09.615
- Back off. Guy!
- Oh.

606
00:41:09.707 --> 00:41:12.333
Make a move. Big Blue.

607
00:41:12.334 --> 00:41:14.370
Guy. relax.

608
00:41:15.337 --> 00:41:17.081
Was the message real or not?

609
00:41:18.007 --> 00:41:20.925
The first half.
The first half is… is real.

610
00:41:20.926 --> 00:41:22.468
The second half was damaged

611
00:41:22.469 --> 00:41:24.429
in the t-trip from Krypton to Earth.

612
00:41:24.430 --> 00:41:26.799
- So it's-it's gotta be doctored.
- No way. Clark.

613
00:41:27.099 --> 00:41:28.808
I know these computer forensics
guys.

614
00:41:28.809 --> 00:41:32.596
They're not gonna say it's legit
unless they are sure.

615
00:41:33.272 --> 00:41:34.898
I'm so sorry. man.

616
00:41:34.899 --> 00:41:36.892
but there's no way that message is fake.

617
00:41:37.610 --> 00:41:39.010
Where'd they get the footage
though?

618
00:41:53.000 --> 00:41:55.502
Are you considering bringing
Superman in for questioning?

619
00:41:55.503 --> 00:41:58.872
We're talking with the President.
and we are reviewing our options now.

620
00:41:58.873 --> 00:42:00.465
I'm sorry. but I have to go.
Miss Lane.

621
00:42:00.466 --> 00:42:01.792
And if you did. when would that--

622
00:42:02.159 --> 00:42:03.176
You buying this?

623
00:42:03.177 --> 00:42:05.045
I don't put anything
past Luthor. Rick.

624
00:42:05.554 --> 00:42:08.056
But the message is authentic.

625
00:42:08.057 --> 00:42:11.851
If the Kryptonian is a danger.
we have to act.

626
00:42:11.852 --> 00:42:12.936
I was a big Superman fan.

627
00:42:12.937 --> 00:42:14.738
I supported him
all the time online and stuff.

628
00:42:14.739 --> 00:42:15.764
but now?

629
00:42:15.765 --> 00:42:17.090
I mean. I hope he rots in hell.

630
00:42:17.091 --> 00:42:18.758
I don't care.
You're supposed to get out!

631
00:42:18.759 --> 00:42:20.560
- Get me some pictures.
- We have a deadline!

632
00:42:20.561 --> 00:42:21.644
Where is he? Get there now!

633
00:42:21.645 --> 00:42:23.847
- Don't call me Chief.
- Okay. I'm gonna do my job.

634
00:42:23.848 --> 00:42:26.157
It's no wonder the Kryptonian

635
00:42:26.158 --> 00:42:30.203
interfered with Boravia's interests.

636
00:42:30.204 --> 00:42:35.041
Boravia wants to save the people
of Jarhanpur.

637
00:42:35.042 --> 00:42:38.787
And Superman
wants to keep them enslaved!

638
00:42:39.338 --> 00:42:44.551
Also. from what I hear.

639
00:42:44.552 --> 00:42:50.723
he finds Boravian women
the most physically attractive

640
00:42:50.724 --> 00:42:55.679
and wants to add them
to his secret harem.

641
00:42:58.023 --> 00:43:00.142
I have a question.
President Ghurkos.

642
00:43:00.901 --> 00:43:02.102
Thank you.

643
00:43:03.988 --> 00:43:07.274
That couldn't
have gone better. Mr. President!

644
00:43:07.491 --> 00:43:10.361
You were so handsome and dynamic!

645
00:43:10.494 --> 00:43:12.154
Wonderful!

646
00:43:12.288 --> 00:43:14.948
Very handsome! Very handsome!

647
00:43:15.916 --> 00:43:18.786
Go! Leave me be!

648
00:43:56.832 --> 00:43:58.374
We did it. Lex!

649
00:43:58.375 --> 00:44:01.377
I wouldn't celebrate until
the alien is off the board.

650
00:44:01.378 --> 00:44:04.130
Oh. here. I brought you a donut.
From Dough's Holes.

651
00:44:04.131 --> 00:44:06.090
New shop in Park Ridge.
of all places.

652
00:44:06.091 --> 00:44:09.427
The fake message.
a stroke of genius.

653
00:44:09.428 --> 00:44:10.445
It's not fake.

654
00:44:10.446 --> 00:44:13.181
He is here to kill us. I knew it!

655
00:44:13.182 --> 00:44:14.432
At Superman's fortress.

656
00:44:14.433 --> 00:44:16.809
I hoped to get the knowledge
to help destroy him.

657
00:44:16.810 --> 00:44:18.228
Little did I know.
his own parents

658
00:44:18.229 --> 00:44:19.680
would be providing it.

659
00:44:19.980 --> 00:44:21.231
Oh.

660
00:44:21.232 --> 00:44:22.524
Right? Yeah.

661
00:44:22.525 --> 00:44:25.352
Been thinking of opening one
in my half of Jarhanpur.

662
00:44:32.701 --> 00:44:36.120
Four. Four. What happened?

663
00:44:36.121 --> 00:44:41.076
I tried to protect Superman.

664
00:44:44.797 --> 00:44:47.924
How did Luthor get in here?
It's keyed into my DNA.

665
00:44:47.925 --> 00:44:51.511
Must protect Superman.

666
00:44:51.512 --> 00:44:54.089
Four.

667
00:44:55.349 --> 00:44:58.677
I'm sorry. friend.

668
00:45:10.072 --> 00:45:11.231
Krypto?

669
00:45:16.203 --> 00:45:17.529
Krypto!

670
00:45:22.501 --> 00:45:23.911
Well. yeah.
that's gonna become--

671
00:45:25.880 --> 00:45:28.298
- Lex. I tried to stop him.
- It's fine. Heather.

672
00:45:28.299 --> 00:45:30.091
Superman. we finally meet.

673
00:45:30.092 --> 00:45:32.177
- Would you like a coffee or tea?
- Where's the dog?

674
00:45:32.178 --> 00:45:33.178
Dog?

675
00:45:33.179 --> 00:45:35.054
The dog. Luthor!
You took the dog!

676
00:45:35.055 --> 00:45:36.924
That's right. Eve. get all of this.

677
00:45:40.811 --> 00:45:42.854
Where's the dog?

678
00:45:42.855 --> 00:45:47.101
I have no clue
what you're talking about.

679
00:45:49.528 --> 00:45:51.988
He's just a dog.

680
00:45:51.989 --> 00:45:54.491
I don't know what dog
you're talking about.

681
00:45:54.492 --> 00:45:55.943
Ugly dog in a cape?

682
00:45:56.368 --> 00:45:57.986
- What did you say?
- Hmm?

683
00:45:58.579 --> 00:46:00.531
I didn't say anything.

684
00:46:00.706 --> 00:46:02.081
You heard what he said!

685
00:46:02.082 --> 00:46:03.625
You heard him! He took him!

686
00:46:03.626 --> 00:46:05.668
I mean. it seems to me.

687
00:46:05.669 --> 00:46:10.006
that the only rabid animal
around here is Superman.

688
00:46:10.007 --> 00:46:13.426
Ever since the discovery
of the Kryptonian's master plan.

689
00:46:13.427 --> 00:46:15.762
he's gone off the deep end.
Thoughts. Chris?

690
00:46:15.763 --> 00:46:17.672
Can't say I'm surprised. Cleavis.

691
00:46:17.673 --> 00:46:19.182
It's guys like this. they always got

692
00:46:19.183 --> 00:46:21.017
a whole bunch of dark. ugly secrets.

693
00:46:21.018 --> 00:46:22.894
What do you mean.
"guys like this?"

694
00:46:22.895 --> 00:46:24.596
Thinks he's better
than everybody else.

695
00:46:25.189 --> 00:46:27.524
Makes this declaration
he's against killing people

696
00:46:27.525 --> 00:46:28.805
unless it's
absolutely necessary.

697
00:46:29.401 --> 00:46:30.401
Really. dude?

698
00:46:30.678 --> 00:46:32.695
It kinda sounds like
you're trying to make the guys

699
00:46:32.696 --> 00:46:34.881
who are a little more
edgier than you look like jerks.

700
00:46:34.882 --> 00:46:36.299
- Know what I mean?
- Mm-hmm.

701
00:46:36.300 --> 00:46:38.868
A lot of these guys. these…

702
00:46:38.869 --> 00:46:40.119
heroes from the magazines.

703
00:46:40.120 --> 00:46:41.538
they're obsessed with me.

704
00:46:41.539 --> 00:46:43.581
'Cause I'm more jacked
than they are.

705
00:46:43.582 --> 00:46:44.662
They know they don't have--

706
00:46:48.546 --> 00:46:50.247
You have a dog?

707
00:46:50.548 --> 00:46:54.376
No. not really. It's more of
a… foster situation.

708
00:47:00.933 --> 00:47:02.342
Cocoa.

709
00:47:08.774 --> 00:47:10.392
You were out there helping them?

710
00:47:14.113 --> 00:47:16.114
Oh. no. that's just. uh--

711
00:47:16.115 --> 00:47:17.483
That's just
some dimensional imp.

712
00:47:18.159 --> 00:47:21.028
They've got that handled.
I was looking for the dog.

713
00:47:28.794 --> 00:47:30.162
You okay?

714
00:47:31.088 --> 00:47:33.540
The footage is not
what it looks like. Lois.

715
00:47:34.592 --> 00:47:35.967
Okay.

716
00:47:35.968 --> 00:47:38.386
The ship my parents sent me in
was damaged in transit.

717
00:47:38.387 --> 00:47:41.256
so I only ever heard
the first part of the message.

718
00:47:42.224 --> 00:47:44.843
And I believed
I knew how it ended.

719
00:47:45.477 --> 00:47:48.730
That my parents had sent me here
to serve the people of Earth

720
00:47:48.731 --> 00:47:50.682
and to be a good man.

721
00:47:52.735 --> 00:47:55.479
I'm not here
to rule over anybody. Lois.

722
00:47:55.779 --> 00:48:00.150
I never thought you were.
even for a moment. Clark.

723
00:48:08.918 --> 00:48:10.327
Oh. that's really good.

724
00:48:11.712 --> 00:48:14.289
I'm sorry we fought.

725
00:48:15.424 --> 00:48:16.500
Me too.

726
00:48:16.759 --> 00:48:18.676
But we're bound to. though.

727
00:48:18.677 --> 00:48:20.879
We're so different.

728
00:48:21.388 --> 00:48:24.633
I was just some punk rock kid
from Bakerline. and you're…

729
00:48:25.518 --> 00:48:26.809
Superman.

730
00:48:26.810 --> 00:48:29.395
- I'm punk rock.
- You are not punk rock.

731
00:48:29.396 --> 00:48:30.980
I like the Strangle-Fellows.

732
00:48:30.981 --> 00:48:33.149
and the P.O.D.s
and the Mighty Crabjoys.

733
00:48:33.150 --> 00:48:35.735
Those are pop radio bands.
They're not punk rock.

734
00:48:35.736 --> 00:48:38.446
The Mighty Crabjoys suck.

735
00:48:38.447 --> 00:48:40.607
Okay. well.
a lot of people love 'em.

736
00:48:43.619 --> 00:48:46.864
My point is. I question
everything and everyone.

737
00:48:47.748 --> 00:48:49.999
You trust everyone

738
00:48:50.000 --> 00:48:53.454
and think everyone
you've ever met is. like…

739
00:48:54.463 --> 00:48:55.914
beautiful.

740
00:48:59.635 --> 00:49:01.879
Maybe that's the real punk rock.

741
00:49:12.690 --> 00:49:15.024
Lois. what did you mean
when you said

742
00:49:15.025 --> 00:49:16.643
that you knew
this would never work?

743
00:49:19.697 --> 00:49:21.065
I don't know.

744
00:49:26.662 --> 00:49:27.787
I'm gonna go.

745
00:49:27.788 --> 00:49:29.998
The DOJ has
a warrant out for my arrest.

746
00:49:29.999 --> 00:49:32.125
so I'm gonna turn myself in.

747
00:49:32.126 --> 00:49:34.578
Wait. what? Why?

748
00:49:34.753 --> 00:49:36.880
Maybe they'll take me
wherever they took the dog.

749
00:49:36.881 --> 00:49:38.289
I don't know
how else to find him.

750
00:49:38.290 --> 00:49:39.315
It's a dog.

751
00:49:39.316 --> 00:49:41.810
Yeah. and he's not even
a very good one. but…

752
00:49:42.595 --> 00:49:44.296
he's out there alone.

753
00:49:44.805 --> 00:49:46.382
And he's probably scared.

754
00:50:03.532 --> 00:50:04.692
I love you. Lois.

755
00:50:06.118 --> 00:50:08.612
I probably should have
told you that a long time ago.

756
00:50:27.223 --> 00:50:28.973
Is that necessary?

757
00:50:28.974 --> 00:50:30.926
I'm coming in on my own accord.

758
00:50:32.811 --> 00:50:34.555
No one read me my rights.

759
00:50:34.813 --> 00:50:36.523
Courts decided
those rights don't apply

760
00:50:36.524 --> 00:50:38.358
to extraterrestrial organisms.

761
00:50:38.359 --> 00:50:39.734
Therefore.
at this point. Superman.

762
00:50:39.735 --> 00:50:41.578
you don't have
any rights to read.

763
00:50:41.579 --> 00:50:43.029
The government
is very well aware

764
00:50:43.030 --> 00:50:45.031
of the potential limitations
detaining you.

765
00:50:45.032 --> 00:50:46.658
so we've outsourced
your confinement

766
00:50:46.659 --> 00:50:48.993
and your interrogation
to PlanetWatch.

767
00:50:48.994 --> 00:50:50.279
PlanetWatch?

768
00:50:51.080 --> 00:50:52.823
I'm sorry about this.

769
00:51:33.747 --> 00:51:34.806
Hey!

770
00:52:00.774 --> 00:52:03.060
Twice in two days.
What a pleasure.

771
00:52:03.569 --> 00:52:04.770
Luthor.

772
00:52:05.654 --> 00:52:07.947
Your obsession with me
is getting a little creepy.

773
00:52:07.948 --> 00:52:10.909
Don't worry. Tall. dark.
and Martian isn't my type.

774
00:52:10.910 --> 00:52:13.112
- Kryptonian.
- Eh. same diff.

775
00:52:21.962 --> 00:52:23.213
Where are we?

776
00:52:23.214 --> 00:52:24.797
A pocket universe.

777
00:52:24.798 --> 00:52:27.592
I replicated the Big Bang
with a LuthorCorp mega-collider.

778
00:52:27.593 --> 00:52:30.671
tearing a tiny hole between
the two universal fabrics.

779
00:52:31.430 --> 00:52:34.474
I'm able to access it from
multiple dimensional portals

780
00:52:34.475 --> 00:52:35.843
I've set up around the globe.

781
00:52:36.644 --> 00:52:40.313
Rex. the metahuman
known as the Element Man.

782
00:52:40.314 --> 00:52:43.107
has been called into service
for a specific purpose.

783
00:52:43.108 --> 00:52:45.944
He can metamorphose
into any known substance.

784
00:52:45.945 --> 00:52:51.025
Even substances foreign
to this planet. like…

785
00:52:58.040 --> 00:53:00.034
…Kryptonite.

786
00:53:02.962 --> 00:53:05.380
Once again.
Vasil Ghurkos is sending troops

787
00:53:05.381 --> 00:53:07.057
to the Jarhanpurian border.

788
00:53:07.058 --> 00:53:08.341
Superman's been
out of commission

789
00:53:08.342 --> 00:53:11.045
less than a day. and already
Boravia's pulling this crap?

790
00:53:11.846 --> 00:53:13.263
- Right?
- What?

791
00:53:13.264 --> 00:53:14.722
Sorry. I'm trying to figure out

792
00:53:14.723 --> 00:53:17.016
how Lex Luthor's
connected to all this.

793
00:53:17.017 --> 00:53:18.017
How's that a mystery?

794
00:53:18.018 --> 00:53:20.812
LuthorCorp sells arms
to Boravia. Boravia goes to war.

795
00:53:20.813 --> 00:53:23.523
Luthor sells more arms
and gets richer than ever.

796
00:53:23.524 --> 00:53:25.275
- Nope.
- No?

797
00:53:25.276 --> 00:53:26.602
Uh-uh.

798
00:53:26.902 --> 00:53:28.653
I have a connection at BodaBank.

799
00:53:28.654 --> 00:53:31.990
Boda handles the transactions
between LuthorCorp and Boravia.

800
00:53:31.991 --> 00:53:33.408
Yes. LuthorCorp sold them

801
00:53:33.409 --> 00:53:35.368
approximately 80 billion
dollars' worth of arms.

802
00:53:35.369 --> 00:53:36.494
but for those arms.

803
00:53:36.495 --> 00:53:39.873
Boravia paid only
1.625 billion dollars.

804
00:53:39.874 --> 00:53:42.250
So Luthor gave them arms
for free? For what?

805
00:53:42.251 --> 00:53:46.957
That's the 78 billion.
375-million-dollar question.

806
00:53:46.958 --> 00:53:48.923
Have you found out
where they're holding Superman?

807
00:53:48.924 --> 00:53:50.600
No one in the government'll say.

808
00:53:50.601 --> 00:53:52.960
Luthor seems to be working
to disable Superman

809
00:53:52.961 --> 00:53:55.822
just so he can't stop
the invasion of Jarhanpur.

810
00:53:55.823 --> 00:53:56.823
Why?

811
00:53:56.974 --> 00:53:58.683
That's way too much sugar. Lois.

812
00:53:58.684 --> 00:54:01.352
I party like a rock star. choir boy.

813
00:54:01.353 --> 00:54:03.472
Still can't hide
the taste of petroleum.

814
00:54:03.689 --> 00:54:04.848
God!

815
00:54:21.790 --> 00:54:23.666
Lex is holding Superman
in a pocket universe.

816
00:54:23.667 --> 00:54:24.692
A what?

817
00:54:24.693 --> 00:54:26.285
I don't know
what a pocket universe is.

818
00:54:26.286 --> 00:54:27.295
Neither does my source.

819
00:54:27.296 --> 00:54:29.547
They don't know anything
about anything. really.

820
00:54:29.548 --> 00:54:31.716
But for sure
he's in a pocket universe.

821
00:54:31.717 --> 00:54:32.884
Who's your source?

822
00:54:32.885 --> 00:54:35.337
I can't say. but you owe me.

823
00:54:35.638 --> 00:54:36.755
Big time.

824
00:54:37.264 --> 00:54:38.424
Like…

825
00:54:39.808 --> 00:54:42.261
I can't even tell you how big.

826
00:54:44.939 --> 00:54:47.065
I love you. Jimmy Olsen.

827
00:54:47.066 --> 00:54:48.726
- I love you.
- Love you.

828
00:55:02.748 --> 00:55:05.834
Just my Monkey-Bots here.
farming outrage 24/7.

829
00:55:05.835 --> 00:55:07.578
Trashing you online.

830
00:55:07.837 --> 00:55:09.663
Hashtag Supershit.

831
00:55:20.140 --> 00:55:21.675
Krypto.

832
00:55:24.186 --> 00:55:26.388
How do you contain a super dog?

833
00:55:27.523 --> 00:55:29.808
You beam super squirrels
into its brain.

834
00:55:31.485 --> 00:55:33.520
We'll learn what we can.

835
00:55:34.238 --> 00:55:37.775
Then we'll put the varmint down.

836
00:55:38.492 --> 00:55:40.444
It will undoubtedly be painful.

837
00:55:41.245 --> 00:55:43.538
Mr. Luthor. please!
I swear…

838
00:55:43.539 --> 00:55:46.492
This is our private
correctional institution.

839
00:55:46.709 --> 00:55:49.002
Yeah. most cells are
rented out to governments

840
00:55:49.003 --> 00:55:51.254
who want to keep
their incarcerations

841
00:55:51.255 --> 00:55:53.965
of political agitators private.

842
00:55:53.966 --> 00:55:56.752
Others are for more
personal transgressions.

843
00:55:56.886 --> 00:55:58.595
Fleurette wrote a blog about me.

844
00:55:58.596 --> 00:56:00.096
There are few things I hate

845
00:56:00.097 --> 00:56:02.800
more than petty ex-girlfriends.

846
00:56:03.075 --> 00:56:04.934
You wouldn't be telling me
any of this if you--

847
00:56:04.935 --> 00:56:07.554
If we ever planned
on letting you out? No.

848
00:56:08.939 --> 00:56:11.350
You'd be terminated
already if it was up to me.

849
00:56:11.567 --> 00:56:13.927
First. the government has some
questions they want answered.

850
00:56:16.906 --> 00:56:20.025
Rex. Look who it is.

851
00:56:28.667 --> 00:56:30.710
You be sure
to keep our guest in check.

852
00:56:30.711 --> 00:56:33.330
Little Joseph certainly
wouldn't want it any other way.

853
00:56:34.381 --> 00:56:36.792
I'll be back tomorrow
to get the answers we need.

854
00:56:41.013 --> 00:56:43.716
Hey. handsome.

855
00:56:47.353 --> 00:56:48.929
Come on over.

856
00:57:01.075 --> 00:57:03.034
- Hi!
- Hey. Eve.

857
00:57:03.035 --> 00:57:04.369
Oh. sorry we had to meet here.

858
00:57:04.370 --> 00:57:06.379
but Lex is always accessing
traffic cameras.

859
00:57:06.380 --> 00:57:07.455
so he knows where I am.

860
00:57:07.456 --> 00:57:09.824
I really don't understand why
you stay in that relationship.

861
00:57:09.825 --> 00:57:12.293
'Cause he made a point to tell
me about all his ex-girlfriends

862
00:57:12.294 --> 00:57:14.053
he had imprisoned
in his pocket universe.

863
00:57:14.054 --> 00:57:15.338
- What?
- Right?

864
00:57:15.339 --> 00:57:17.340
- How's your mom?
- My mom?

865
00:57:17.341 --> 00:57:18.466
Oh. I love her so much.

866
00:57:18.467 --> 00:57:21.135
I think of her as my mom.
even more than my own mother.

867
00:57:21.136 --> 00:57:22.762
Oh. she feels the same way.

868
00:57:22.763 --> 00:57:24.889
from the-the one time
that you guys met.

869
00:57:24.890 --> 00:57:26.349
- Yeah?
- So. hey. Okay.

870
00:57:26.350 --> 00:57:27.942
- Yes. Yes.
- Eve?

871
00:57:27.943 --> 00:57:29.602
There seems to be
some sort of connection

872
00:57:29.603 --> 00:57:31.855
between Boravia and your boyfriend.

873
00:57:31.856 --> 00:57:33.182
-I'm not clear on what--
-Oh.

874
00:57:33.315 --> 00:57:34.315
What's wrong?

875
00:57:34.650 --> 00:57:36.018
What's "oh"?

876
00:57:36.151 --> 00:57:38.486
I thought you wanted
to see me. Jimmy.

877
00:57:38.487 --> 00:57:39.571
I do but. Eve.

878
00:57:39.572 --> 00:57:42.657
how could I even really see you
with Lex still in the picture?

879
00:57:42.658 --> 00:57:44.592
You're just trying
to get information out of me.

880
00:57:44.593 --> 00:57:45.802
I swear to God. that's not it.

881
00:57:45.803 --> 00:57:48.012
I-I just know that if I could
get some real dirt on him.

882
00:57:48.013 --> 00:57:49.539
then maybe the two of us could--

883
00:57:49.540 --> 00:57:51.200
Could be together again?

884
00:57:56.839 --> 00:57:58.040
Yeah.

885
00:57:59.450 --> 00:58:00.742
But you said my toes look like

886
00:58:00.743 --> 00:58:02.510
someone spilled
shrimp cocktail on the floor.

887
00:58:02.511 --> 00:58:04.721
You have unconventional toes.
Who cares?

888
00:58:04.722 --> 00:58:06.530
There's other parts of you
that people would

889
00:58:06.531 --> 00:58:08.024
find very attractive.

890
00:58:08.025 --> 00:58:09.876
Lex tortured a dog the other day.

891
00:58:10.144 --> 00:58:12.270
- Jesus Christ!
- I know.

892
00:58:12.271 --> 00:58:14.139
- I have to go.
- Eve.

893
00:58:14.857 --> 00:58:16.558
Please see
what you can find out.

894
00:58:17.443 --> 00:58:19.978
- Okay.
- Yes! Yes!

895
00:58:21.113 --> 00:58:22.398
Okay.

896
00:58:24.867 --> 00:58:26.284
I'm-I'm putting 'em in my pocket.

897
00:58:26.285 --> 00:58:28.153
Okay.

898
00:58:37.963 --> 00:58:40.340
Joseph. He's your son?

899
00:58:40.341 --> 00:58:41.542
Don't talk to me.

900
00:58:42.009 --> 00:58:43.009
Please.

901
00:58:45.054 --> 00:58:48.348
I could fly over and get him
if you just--

902
00:58:48.349 --> 00:58:49.732
if you'd stop
with the Kryptonite.

903
00:58:49.733 --> 00:58:51.684
There's no way out of here.
okay? So. just…

904
00:58:51.685 --> 00:58:53.804
- There's always a way.
- I said don't talk to me!

905
00:58:55.064 --> 00:58:56.064
I told you.

906
00:58:58.025 --> 00:58:59.685
Don't talk to me!

907
00:59:09.520 --> 00:59:10.954
Yeah.
so what do you want me to do?

908
00:59:10.955 --> 00:59:12.038
Where's the creamer?

909
00:59:12.039 --> 00:59:13.957
On the counter.
where it always is.

910
00:59:13.958 --> 00:59:17.043
He's in your group. right?
The. um. uh--

911
00:59:17.044 --> 00:59:19.045
- What's it called. again?
- The Justice Gang.

912
00:59:19.046 --> 00:59:20.630
- No.
- We're not called that.

913
00:59:20.631 --> 00:59:22.131
Yeah. your name is Mr. Terrific.

914
00:59:22.132 --> 00:59:23.858
You don't get a vote
with a name like that.

915
00:59:23.859 --> 00:59:25.818
I also voted against it.

916
00:59:25.819 --> 00:59:28.405
Yes. And as leader.
I get tiebreaker.

917
00:59:28.406 --> 00:59:31.606
- No. Superman is not officially a member.
- Because you don't want him to vote.

918
00:59:31.607 --> 00:59:32.889
You know
which way that would go.

919
00:59:32.890 --> 00:59:33.977
Shut up. He's kidding.

920
00:59:33.978 --> 00:59:37.222
So. how do you even know
Superman anyway?

921
00:59:37.982 --> 00:59:40.149
I… just… do.

922
00:59:40.150 --> 00:59:41.818
So you know
about the hypno-glasses?

923
00:59:41.819 --> 00:59:43.027
Now she does.

924
00:59:43.028 --> 00:59:46.431
I'm not saying who he is. just
that he wears hypno-glasses.

925
00:59:46.432 --> 00:59:47.448
They make his face…

926
00:59:47.449 --> 00:59:48.575
Terrific. how do they work?

927
00:59:48.576 --> 00:59:50.118
They make his face
look different

928
00:59:50.119 --> 00:59:51.703
in your brain
when he wears them.

929
00:59:51.704 --> 00:59:52.987
So that you don't know
who he is.

930
00:59:52.988 --> 00:59:54.581
Yes. I know this. first of all.

931
00:59:54.582 --> 00:59:56.941
But. second of all. you really
shouldn't be telling me this

932
00:59:56.942 --> 00:59:59.043
in case I don't know who he is.

933
00:59:59.044 --> 01:00:00.378
So. you know he's Clark Kent?

934
01:00:00.379 --> 01:00:03.339
Oh. my God.
Why does he trust everyone?

935
01:00:03.340 --> 01:00:07.169
He doesn't. Just us because
we are also of the cloth.

936
01:00:08.262 --> 01:00:09.588
"Of the cloth?"

937
01:00:11.599 --> 01:00:14.301
- What are we gonna do?
- About what?

938
01:00:14.393 --> 01:00:17.270
Superman! He's your friend!

939
01:00:17.271 --> 01:00:19.606
Some friend.
Came here to rule over me?

940
01:00:19.607 --> 01:00:21.475
It would be difficult
to find him.

941
01:00:21.859 --> 01:00:25.737
I put nanobot GPS trackers
into Superman's bloodstream.

942
01:00:25.738 --> 01:00:27.447
You can see where his trail ends

943
01:00:27.448 --> 01:00:29.073
abruptly right here at Fort Kramer.

944
01:00:29.074 --> 01:00:32.035
a dormant military post across
the river about ten miles down.

945
01:00:32.036 --> 01:00:34.746
Even if he was dead. those
trackers would still be there.

946
01:00:34.747 --> 01:00:36.456
So. all this leads me to believe.

947
01:00:36.457 --> 01:00:37.790
as your article surmised.

948
01:00:37.791 --> 01:00:39.243
he really is in a pocket universe.

949
01:00:40.377 --> 01:00:43.546
You put nanobot GPS trackers
in your friend's bloodstream?

950
01:00:43.547 --> 01:00:45.207
Oh. I do that to everybody.

951
01:00:45.549 --> 01:00:48.218
So. okay. Come on.
Let's go to Fort Kramer then.

952
01:00:48.219 --> 01:00:50.011
The four of us.
and find out what's going on.

953
01:00:50.012 --> 01:00:52.214
And then do what?

954
01:00:52.640 --> 01:00:54.425
Save him.

955
01:00:54.725 --> 01:00:56.100
You wanna break a federally

956
01:00:56.101 --> 01:00:58.061
incarcerated prisoner
out of jail?

957
01:00:58.062 --> 01:00:59.729
Look. I think this is being done

958
01:00:59.730 --> 01:01:01.981
to keep him from interfering
with the Boravian invasion.

959
01:01:01.982 --> 01:01:04.484
No. you look.
I'm a Green Lantern. lady.

960
01:01:04.485 --> 01:01:07.070
That means I took a vow
not to get involved in politics.

961
01:01:07.071 --> 01:01:08.363
Oh. that's part of the vows?

962
01:01:08.364 --> 01:01:09.831
It's implied. Yeah.

963
01:01:09.832 --> 01:01:10.882
An implied vow?

964
01:01:10.883 --> 01:01:12.900
Every time there's something
he doesn't want to do.

965
01:01:12.901 --> 01:01:14.185
he says it's part of some vow.

966
01:01:14.186 --> 01:01:15.211
Oh. I swear to God.

967
01:01:15.212 --> 01:01:17.430
I am two seconds away
from forming a giant hammer.

968
01:01:17.431 --> 01:01:18.882
and beating you both to death.

969
01:01:19.625 --> 01:01:21.751
Is Supes here
to take over the world?

970
01:01:21.752 --> 01:01:23.169
I don't know. Probably not.

971
01:01:23.170 --> 01:01:25.088
But the risk
is just not worth the beef

972
01:01:25.089 --> 01:01:27.298
between the US government
and the Justice Gang.

973
01:01:27.299 --> 01:01:29.259
Not our name.
Makes us sound like cowboys.

974
01:01:29.260 --> 01:01:31.378
But I agree with the rest.

975
01:01:32.012 --> 01:01:33.930
So you're just gonna
let your friend rot

976
01:01:33.931 --> 01:01:35.924
in a pocket universe?

977
01:01:48.737 --> 01:01:51.281
That haircut should be
against your vows.

978
01:01:51.282 --> 01:01:52.608
That what?

979
01:01:53.367 --> 01:01:55.034
That what should be what?

980
01:01:55.035 --> 01:01:59.073
I'll have you know
348 chicks say otherwise.

981
01:02:04.753 --> 01:02:05.753
Hey!

982
01:02:08.591 --> 01:02:09.591
What?

983
01:02:09.633 --> 01:02:11.668
I'm not saying
we're gonna save him. but…

984
01:02:12.311 --> 01:02:14.345
…I think we can at least
check out what's going on

985
01:02:14.346 --> 01:02:16.306
with your boyfriend
at this Fort Kramer.

986
01:02:16.307 --> 01:02:17.341
He's not--

987
01:02:18.225 --> 01:02:19.760
We're just seeing each other.

988
01:02:20.519 --> 01:02:21.519
But thanks.

989
01:02:21.812 --> 01:02:23.097
You want me to drive?

990
01:02:25.065 --> 01:02:26.600
We'll take my ride.

991
01:02:46.921 --> 01:02:48.296
You have a flying saucer.

992
01:02:48.297 --> 01:02:50.624
but you couldn't get
a faster garage door?

993
01:02:51.300 --> 01:02:52.876
I haven't worked on that yet.

994
01:02:54.678 --> 01:02:57.381
I'm not even sure how I feel.
Honestly.

995
01:02:57.681 --> 01:03:00.300
- What?
- About Clark.

996
01:03:00.359 --> 01:03:01.860
He's not my boyfriend.

997
01:03:01.861 --> 01:03:03.611
We've actually just been
seeing each other…

998
01:03:03.612 --> 01:03:05.922
-Yeah. lady. just to be clear.
-…for a couple of months--

999
01:03:05.923 --> 01:03:07.506
I'm not into people's emotions.

1000
01:03:07.507 --> 01:03:09.150
Yeah. no. totally.

1001
01:03:09.151 --> 01:03:10.561
I'm just thinking out loud.

1002
01:03:10.986 --> 01:03:12.695
I was gonna
break up with him. actually.

1003
01:03:12.696 --> 01:03:14.489
I mean. we had this huge fight.

1004
01:03:14.490 --> 01:03:17.192
and he told me he loved me.
and it just didn't…

1005
01:03:26.043 --> 01:03:28.620
Q&A time. alien.

1006
01:03:32.466 --> 01:03:34.384
Today we have a special guest.

1007
01:03:34.385 --> 01:03:37.713
I'm familiar with him.

1008
01:03:39.557 --> 01:03:43.434
And the smell of his piss
as we flew across the desert.

1009
01:03:43.435 --> 01:03:44.853
That is a lie!

1010
01:03:44.854 --> 01:03:47.598
No. not Vasil.
He's just here as an observer.

1011
01:03:50.234 --> 01:03:52.151
Mali.

1012
01:03:52.152 --> 01:03:56.531
Now. the US government
has a few questions for you.

1013
01:03:56.532 --> 01:03:59.860
Luthor. I barely know him.
He gave me food one time.

1014
01:04:00.995 --> 01:04:03.197
Who are you working with
here on Earth?

1015
01:04:04.081 --> 01:04:05.748
I'm not working
with anyone. Luthor.

1016
01:04:05.749 --> 01:04:07.250
Don't tell him nothing.
Superman.

1017
01:04:07.251 --> 01:04:08.543
I have no family or nothing.

1018
01:04:08.544 --> 01:04:09.627
Luthor. don't do this.

1019
01:04:09.628 --> 01:04:11.663
You eating my food
was a great honor. Superman.

1020
01:04:12.548 --> 01:04:13.798
- Ooh.
- No.

1021
01:04:13.799 --> 01:04:15.667
- Got lucky on that one.
- No. please.

1022
01:04:17.094 --> 01:04:18.887
No. Luthor.
don't do this. Please.

1023
01:04:18.888 --> 01:04:21.014
Let's try another question.
shall we. Superman?

1024
01:04:21.015 --> 01:04:23.600
- Luthor. don't do this.
- Who raised you as a child?

1025
01:04:23.601 --> 01:04:25.310
- I can't.
- I believe in you. Superman!

1026
01:04:25.311 --> 01:04:26.678
- No!
- Don't tell him--

1027
01:04:37.281 --> 01:04:39.149
I didn't imagine
that would go so quickly.

1028
01:04:39.450 --> 01:04:42.861
I'm sorry. it's…

1029
01:04:45.956 --> 01:04:47.157
Mr. Handsome.

1030
01:04:48.434 --> 01:04:50.752
I'll be back later with someone
else you've chatted with.

1031
01:04:50.753 --> 01:04:52.079
and I'll kill them too.

1032
01:04:52.755 --> 01:04:55.666
Maybe that reporter
you always do interviews with.

1033
01:04:55.966 --> 01:04:58.669
Maybe I'll kill Clark Kent next.

1034
01:05:09.939 --> 01:05:12.474
No. no. no. no.

1035
01:05:42.763 --> 01:05:44.472
Restricted area. pal!

1036
01:05:44.473 --> 01:05:46.633
Get back to your vehicle
and get out of here!

1037
01:05:47.059 --> 01:05:48.643
Whoa! What do we got here?

1038
01:05:48.644 --> 01:05:50.512
Hey! You see this guy?

1039
01:05:51.105 --> 01:05:52.814
Unbelievable.

1040
01:05:52.815 --> 01:05:54.065
- Hey!
- Um…

1041
01:05:54.066 --> 01:05:55.525
You at the wrong address. bro.

1042
01:05:55.526 --> 01:05:56.651
That's his path.

1043
01:05:56.652 --> 01:05:58.278
DNA trail leads to that tent.

1044
01:05:58.279 --> 01:05:59.295
Keep moving. clown.

1045
01:05:59.296 --> 01:06:00.905
Isn't that one of those
Justice guys?

1046
01:06:00.906 --> 01:06:02.198
It's just the smart one.

1047
01:06:02.199 --> 01:06:05.118
Hey! You heard the man.

1048
01:06:05.119 --> 01:06:08.705
I am giving you
one last chance to stop!

1049
01:06:08.706 --> 01:06:10.623
I was just about to
say the same to you.

1050
01:06:10.624 --> 01:06:12.292
Fire!

1051
01:06:19.300 --> 01:06:21.293
Fall back! Fall back!

1052
01:06:21.844 --> 01:06:22.961
Get out of the way!

1053
01:06:23.762 --> 01:06:25.005
Cover me!

1054
01:06:28.225 --> 01:06:30.094
Flank right!

1055
01:06:46.202 --> 01:06:47.553
Look out!

1056
01:07:17.191 --> 01:07:18.767
Holy shit.

1057
01:07:28.911 --> 01:07:30.487
Unbelievable.

1058
01:07:31.080 --> 01:07:33.282
That jackass
did create a pocket universe.

1059
01:07:33.874 --> 01:07:35.701
And that's… bad?

1060
01:07:36.460 --> 01:07:39.963
When creating a pocket universe.
if you are just one picometer off.

1061
01:07:39.964 --> 01:07:42.966
you will have a black hole
where Earth used to be.

1062
01:07:42.967 --> 01:07:45.093
And every time
you enter or exit.

1063
01:07:45.094 --> 01:07:47.379
you risk tearing a hole
in the fabric of reality.

1064
01:07:47.888 --> 01:07:49.305
You're kidding.

1065
01:07:49.306 --> 01:07:50.631
It's the type
of reckless science

1066
01:07:50.632 --> 01:07:52.475
Lex Luthor specializes in.

1067
01:07:52.476 --> 01:07:53.802
What are they doing?

1068
01:07:54.228 --> 01:07:55.679
They're trying to hack it.

1069
01:07:56.230 --> 01:07:58.140
So. I guess you decided to help.

1070
01:07:59.400 --> 01:08:01.769
Only because
it'll piss off Green Lantern.

1071
01:08:04.029 --> 01:08:05.064
Thanks.

1072
01:08:12.580 --> 01:08:14.615
He just killed that poor guy.

1073
01:08:15.416 --> 01:08:18.535
Mali. His name was Mali.

1074
01:08:18.836 --> 01:08:21.955
And I didn't… I-- I didn't…

1075
01:08:22.882 --> 01:08:24.707
I didn't do anything.

1076
01:08:30.055 --> 01:08:31.881
You said
you can get to my son. right?

1077
01:08:56.916 --> 01:09:01.495
Ooh.

1078
01:09:10.054 --> 01:09:11.638
Why are you still gross-looking?

1079
01:09:11.639 --> 01:09:13.924
I don't know.

1080
01:09:14.641 --> 01:09:15.925
I thought that…

1081
01:09:17.102 --> 01:09:18.686
It must be the sun.

1082
01:09:18.687 --> 01:09:21.397
What are you-- What sun?
There's no sun here.

1083
01:09:21.398 --> 01:09:23.434
That's the problem.
I need to heal.

1084
01:09:23.984 --> 01:09:26.486
I get my powers
from the yellow sun.

1085
01:09:26.487 --> 01:09:28.897
Just… give me a second.

1086
01:09:33.077 --> 01:09:34.318
Come on!

1087
01:09:37.957 --> 01:09:40.367
Hell. yeah. We're in.

1088
01:09:58.936 --> 01:10:02.264
Whoa! An antiproton river.

1089
01:10:06.277 --> 01:10:09.063
- Do we rappel?
- Rappel?

1090
01:10:09.472 --> 01:10:11.072
Where am I gonna get
the gear to rappel

1091
01:10:11.073 --> 01:10:12.532
into a pocket universe?

1092
01:10:12.533 --> 01:10:14.217
I don't know.
Maybe it comes out of your…

1093
01:10:14.218 --> 01:10:15.635
circles or something.

1094
01:10:15.636 --> 01:10:16.803
- Circles?
- What?

1095
01:10:16.804 --> 01:10:18.246
- T-spheres.
- Okay.

1096
01:10:18.247 --> 01:10:20.115
They're three-dimensional.
Circles are flat.

1097
01:10:20.457 --> 01:10:21.492
Sorry.

1098
01:10:22.001 --> 01:10:24.995
Unbelievable.

1099
01:10:25.337 --> 01:10:27.755
This place is filthy
with black hole vortexes.

1100
01:10:27.756 --> 01:10:30.417
and that antiproton river
will tear us apart in seconds.

1101
01:10:30.551 --> 01:10:32.503
We cannot go in ourselves.

1102
01:10:33.596 --> 01:10:34.880
Copy.

1103
01:10:35.389 --> 01:10:37.007
I can't make a sun.

1104
01:10:37.541 --> 01:10:38.600
I know.

1105
01:10:38.601 --> 01:10:41.595
I can only make something
kind of like a sun.

1106
01:10:41.896 --> 01:10:43.931
- What?
- All right.

1107
01:10:44.590 --> 01:10:45.607
Okay.

1108
01:10:45.608 --> 01:10:49.144
Okay.
we got hydrogen. and deuterium.

1109
01:10:49.820 --> 01:10:51.112
And we got helium.

1110
01:10:51.113 --> 01:10:53.189
- And compression. obviously.
- What are you doing?

1111
01:10:53.190 --> 01:10:55.150
Hey! Hey. no. no. Stop!

1112
01:10:55.151 --> 01:10:57.327
Enough! You're. you're gonna
get all of us in trouble!

1113
01:10:57.328 --> 01:10:59.287
Hey. bro. what are you doing?
Stop that!

1114
01:10:59.288 --> 01:11:00.788
He's doing something in here!

1115
01:11:00.789 --> 01:11:03.274
Guards! Guards!
He's doing something!

1116
01:11:03.275 --> 01:11:05.110
No. you are not going
to take credit for this.

1117
01:11:05.111 --> 01:11:06.419
I am the one that saw it first.

1118
01:11:06.420 --> 01:11:07.670
Oh. take a hike. Barbie!

1119
01:11:07.671 --> 01:11:09.405
- I'm getting the credit for it!
- Barbie?

1120
01:11:09.406 --> 01:11:10.781
These two are gonna
get us killed!

1121
01:11:10.782 --> 01:11:11.849
Guards! Guards!

1122
01:11:11.850 --> 01:11:14.344
- Raptors! Raptors!
- In here! Guards! Guards!

1123
01:11:14.345 --> 01:11:16.630
I'm seeing something
that you'd all wanna see!

1124
01:11:55.886 --> 01:11:57.171
Joey!

1125
01:12:00.516 --> 01:12:01.550
You have to take him.

1126
01:12:01.976 --> 01:12:04.011
I can't carry him
when I change forms.

1127
01:12:13.529 --> 01:12:15.647
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
No. no. no! Krypto! Krypto!

1128
01:12:16.448 --> 01:12:18.199
Stop! Krypto! Krypto! Stop!

1129
01:12:18.200 --> 01:12:20.652
You're gonna
squash the baby. Stop!

1130
01:12:22.121 --> 01:12:24.198
What do you see?
Did you find him?

1131
01:12:24.456 --> 01:12:27.167
Oh. my God! What is that?

1132
01:12:27.168 --> 01:12:28.877
Portal's been open too long.

1133
01:12:28.878 --> 01:12:31.038
We can't stand here much longer.

1134
01:12:33.424 --> 01:12:35.175
Aw. you look like shit.

1135
01:12:35.176 --> 01:12:36.451
I'm fine.

1136
01:12:36.452 --> 01:12:38.386
I think we need to get to
those portals up there.

1137
01:12:38.387 --> 01:12:40.722
Uh. right. How do we…

1138
01:12:40.723 --> 01:12:41.931
…work them?

1139
01:12:41.932 --> 01:12:43.634
I don't know.
but we'll figure it out.

1140
01:12:43.726 --> 01:12:44.726
Yeah.

1141
01:12:47.104 --> 01:12:48.222
Joey!

1142
01:13:11.128 --> 01:13:12.538
Kill him! He's still weak!

1143
01:13:21.096 --> 01:13:24.550
All right. freak. Nice and slow.
Back in the cage.

1144
01:13:25.726 --> 01:13:27.720
What are you gonna do.
splash us?

1145
01:13:28.437 --> 01:13:31.640
Yes. With fluoroantimonic acid.

1146
01:13:55.798 --> 01:13:57.458
Do you have him?

1147
01:13:58.008 --> 01:14:00.169
- Hot damn.
- What?

1148
01:14:00.511 --> 01:14:01.879
It's a flying dog.

1149
01:14:04.348 --> 01:14:05.966
- Uh-oh.
- What?

1150
01:14:07.977 --> 01:14:09.219
Come on. come on!

1151
01:14:10.229 --> 01:14:11.472
No. no. no! No!

1152
01:14:33.669 --> 01:14:35.454
Black hole!

1153
01:14:42.887 --> 01:14:44.296
Oh. boy!

1154
01:14:45.848 --> 01:14:47.549
Krypto! Come here. boy!

1155
01:14:47.850 --> 01:14:49.093
I can't get out of this!

1156
01:14:49.393 --> 01:14:50.393
Krypto!

1157
01:14:50.811 --> 01:14:52.687
It's a black hole!
We'll never get out of it!

1158
01:14:52.688 --> 01:14:53.806
Pull us out!

1159
01:14:54.565 --> 01:14:56.517
Krypto! Come!

1160
01:14:58.277 --> 01:15:01.021
Stop it! Krypto! Help us out!

1161
01:15:01.363 --> 01:15:02.606
Bad boy!

1162
01:15:05.159 --> 01:15:06.159
Rex!

1163
01:15:07.328 --> 01:15:08.445
Joey!

1164
01:15:47.159 --> 01:15:49.820
Man. you are so weird.

1165
01:15:52.748 --> 01:15:55.041
- Do you have him?
- Them.

1166
01:15:55.042 --> 01:15:56.459
Superman. a mean dog in a cape.

1167
01:15:56.460 --> 01:15:59.079
a weird baby.
and a squiggle man.

1168
01:15:59.672 --> 01:16:00.672
What?

1169
01:16:02.383 --> 01:16:04.877
- Terrific?
- Follow me!

1170
01:16:09.181 --> 01:16:11.925
Krypto! No! Leave it!

1171
01:16:28.200 --> 01:16:30.277
Are you kidding me?

1172
01:16:31.620 --> 01:16:33.781
Those things aren't cheap!

1173
01:16:38.919 --> 01:16:41.171
Oh. my gosh. Thank you.

1174
01:16:41.172 --> 01:16:43.207
Hey. buddy.

1175
01:16:45.593 --> 01:16:48.504
Hey. Hey.

1176
01:16:52.057 --> 01:16:54.718
- You came to get me.
- Yeah.

1177
01:16:58.355 --> 01:17:01.683
There's more people…
being held prisoner in there.

1178
01:17:01.942 --> 01:17:03.067
We gotta go get 'em.

1179
01:17:03.068 --> 01:17:04.185
- Whoa.
- Whoa. whoa. whoa.

1180
01:17:04.186 --> 01:17:07.280
Not through here. you can't.
Not with you like this.

1181
01:17:07.281 --> 01:17:09.149
Clark. what the--

1182
01:17:09.492 --> 01:17:10.818
It's Kryptonite poisoning.

1183
01:17:12.203 --> 01:17:14.204
He'll heal.
but it'll take a day or two.

1184
01:17:14.205 --> 01:17:17.032
Get him someplace safe.
Take the T-craft.

1185
01:17:17.208 --> 01:17:19.792
The controls
are easy and intuitive.

1186
01:17:19.793 --> 01:17:22.371
I need to stay back here and
make sure the portal is secure.

1187
01:17:38.312 --> 01:17:41.473
Okay… okay.

1188
01:17:42.107 --> 01:17:44.101
Okay.

1189
01:17:45.319 --> 01:17:46.611
Okay.

1190
01:17:46.612 --> 01:17:49.197
No. Dog? Dog. I really need to--

1191
01:17:49.198 --> 01:17:51.734
No. Dog. I really need you to--

1192
01:17:52.159 --> 01:17:54.028
Come on.

1193
01:17:55.246 --> 01:17:58.449
Okay. Intuitive.

1194
01:17:58.582 --> 01:18:00.325
Yeah. For sure.

1195
01:18:02.169 --> 01:18:03.245
Okay.

1196
01:18:03.462 --> 01:18:04.663
That's it.

1197
01:18:07.591 --> 01:18:09.793
Whoa!

1198
01:18:16.934 --> 01:18:18.218
Pick that up!

1199
01:18:21.230 --> 01:18:24.349
Eve! Get out of here. you idiot!

1200
01:18:27.653 --> 01:18:28.729
Go!

1201
01:18:29.155 --> 01:18:30.397
Move!

1202
01:18:31.365 --> 01:18:34.735
How the hell
could he have gotten free? Hmm?

1203
01:18:37.538 --> 01:18:39.490
We need to find him.

1204
01:18:44.954 --> 01:18:46.045
Eve?

1205
01:18:46.046 --> 01:18:48.798
Oh. I'm so done. Jimmy.

1206
01:18:48.799 --> 01:18:50.133
Oh. um…

1207
01:18:50.134 --> 01:18:53.186
I have everything you need
to ruin Lex forever.

1208
01:18:53.187 --> 01:18:54.262
What? Where?

1209
01:18:54.263 --> 01:18:56.298
Oh. I have it right here.

1210
01:18:59.101 --> 01:19:01.845
How dare he
throw a pencil at me?

1211
01:19:02.771 --> 01:19:06.058
He's gonna regret harming me
for the rest of his life.

1212
01:19:07.067 --> 01:19:08.519
Such a jerk.

1213
01:19:14.950 --> 01:19:16.318
But if I send you this. Jimmy…

1214
01:19:17.161 --> 01:19:18.904
Uh-huh.

1215
01:19:21.123 --> 01:19:24.326
You have to promise me
we get to hang this weekend.

1216
01:19:24.585 --> 01:19:26.870
Just the two of us.

1217
01:19:30.466 --> 01:19:32.209
Uh…

1218
01:19:35.304 --> 01:19:37.798
- Okay.
- Yeah? Okay! Yay!

1219
01:19:38.724 --> 01:19:42.219
Uh-huh. How. uh… How long?

1220
01:19:43.103 --> 01:19:45.472
- All weekend.
- All weekend?

1221
01:19:45.648 --> 01:19:46.940
Oh. my God. Jimmy!

1222
01:19:46.941 --> 01:19:49.601
I'm sorry this is such
a major imposition on your life!

1223
01:19:49.735 --> 01:19:52.111
No. it's not an imposition. I--

1224
01:19:52.112 --> 01:19:53.897
I can tell
you don't really think so.

1225
01:19:56.283 --> 01:19:58.819
-No. no. no. no. no--
-Eve?

1226
01:20:10.798 --> 01:20:13.042
Come on. Eve.

1227
01:20:27.773 --> 01:20:30.066
I'm-- I'm Martha. This is Jon.

1228
01:20:30.067 --> 01:20:33.187
- I'm Lois. Hi.
- Lois.

1229
01:20:40.369 --> 01:20:41.369
Here. Son.

1230
01:20:42.788 --> 01:20:43.989
Hi. Ma.

1231
01:20:44.540 --> 01:20:46.784
Ma. they sent me here
to rule over everyone.

1232
01:20:47.418 --> 01:20:48.786
They sent me here
to kill people.

1233
01:20:49.086 --> 01:20:51.622
Clark. that ain't-- that ain't…

1234
01:21:16.363 --> 01:21:19.942
Is our boy gonna be okay?

1235
01:21:20.409 --> 01:21:23.654
Yes. Mr. Terrific says yes.

1236
01:21:25.623 --> 01:21:27.741
Don't mind him. Lois.

1237
01:21:28.250 --> 01:21:30.460
He's just a big ol' mush.

1238
01:21:30.461 --> 01:21:33.288
Especially
when it comes to Clark.

1239
01:21:49.146 --> 01:21:51.731
This girl is obsessed with you?

1240
01:21:51.732 --> 01:21:52.741
Uh-huh.

1241
01:21:53.042 --> 01:21:54.543
How do you do it. Jimmy?

1242
01:21:54.544 --> 01:21:56.177
Look. I didn't even want to bother you.

1243
01:21:56.178 --> 01:21:58.208
but you told me to call
with anything I got. so I--

1244
01:21:58.209 --> 01:22:00.490
Yeah. but I thought you said
she disappeared off the line.

1245
01:22:00.491 --> 01:22:02.892
I don't know. She might have
dropped her phone in the toilet.

1246
01:22:02.893 --> 01:22:04.410
She does that a lot.

1247
01:22:04.411 --> 01:22:08.032
Well. I'm not really sure
that sexy selfies are--

1248
01:22:19.635 --> 01:22:21.670
Your hot ex is a genius.

1249
01:22:21.929 --> 01:22:23.763
- Hot?
- We have to talk to Perry.

1250
01:22:23.764 --> 01:22:25.716
I'll be there as soon as I can.
okay?

1251
01:22:28.185 --> 01:22:31.396
Sending sexy selfies
behind the back of Lex Luthor?

1252
01:22:31.397 --> 01:22:34.016
She has to be the biggest idiot
in the world.

1253
01:22:34.158 --> 01:22:36.785
Lex. he just told you.
the portal was destroyed!

1254
01:22:36.786 --> 01:22:38.361
The dimensional aperture
is still there…

1255
01:22:38.362 --> 01:22:39.362
Syd. tell him!

1256
01:22:39.363 --> 01:22:40.929
…which we can open remotely.
so open it.

1257
01:22:40.930 --> 01:22:42.198
It is not… safe!

1258
01:22:42.199 --> 01:22:43.908
We can close the aperture later

1259
01:22:43.909 --> 01:22:45.660
by inputting
the coordinates. correct?

1260
01:22:45.661 --> 01:22:47.363
- Theoretically.
- Great!

1261
01:22:48.831 --> 01:22:52.242
If we can't find him.
we'll need to draw him out.

1262
01:23:11.896 --> 01:23:13.521
But Lex. that could tear

1263
01:23:13.522 --> 01:23:16.149
a dimensional rift
into the surrounding area!

1264
01:23:16.150 --> 01:23:18.352
This is something
you think I don't know?

1265
01:23:22.198 --> 01:23:25.609
- That shouldn't happen.
- Oh. you don't say!

1266
01:23:25.951 --> 01:23:29.988
- Can you… Can you stop it?
- Can I stop it?

1267
01:23:35.794 --> 01:23:40.165
This is why you don't create
a damn pocket universe.

1268
01:23:40.257 --> 01:23:43.085
There. Superman
won't be able to ignore that.

1269
01:23:45.179 --> 01:23:47.256
Now we know where he'll be next.

1270
01:24:29.014 --> 01:24:31.550
Thought you was out here.

1271
01:24:32.726 --> 01:24:33.802
Hey. Pa.

1272
01:24:34.603 --> 01:24:37.598
Never seen you sleep that long.

1273
01:24:41.777 --> 01:24:46.990
Last week me. Ma.
Hector and them.

1274
01:24:46.991 --> 01:24:50.410
we took a drive
to Beerki's Burritos

1275
01:24:50.411 --> 01:24:51.945
down in Luttus.

1276
01:24:52.788 --> 01:24:55.790
Like the one that used to be out
by that old. uh. blue barn.

1277
01:24:55.791 --> 01:24:57.743
out on that I-9.
you remember that?

1278
01:24:58.669 --> 01:25:03.040
- Mm-hmm.
- Burritos still just as good.

1279
01:25:07.553 --> 01:25:10.255
That Louanne.
she-- she seems nice.

1280
01:25:10.723 --> 01:25:13.175
- It's Lois.
- Hmm?

1281
01:25:13.350 --> 01:25:14.635
Her name's Lois.

1282
01:25:15.060 --> 01:25:16.970
But yeah. she's… she's nice.

1283
01:25:18.939 --> 01:25:21.350
But you don't seem
quite yourself.

1284
01:25:23.068 --> 01:25:25.862
Yeah. well. that message
that my parents sent with me.

1285
01:25:25.863 --> 01:25:28.148
I had never heard
the second half before.

1286
01:25:28.782 --> 01:25:33.286
Well. I'd say what you wanted
that message to mean

1287
01:25:33.287 --> 01:25:35.246
says a whole lot more about you

1288
01:25:35.247 --> 01:25:38.374
than what anyone meant
for it to mean.

1289
01:25:38.375 --> 01:25:40.160
Pa. you don't understand.

1290
01:25:43.464 --> 01:25:45.666
I'm not who I thought I was.

1291
01:25:50.721 --> 01:25:52.589
They sent me here
to hurt people.

1292
01:25:53.349 --> 01:25:55.475
Parents aren't for
telling their children

1293
01:25:55.476 --> 01:25:57.136
who they're supposed to be.

1294
01:25:58.479 --> 01:26:01.147
We are here to give y'aII tools.

1295
01:26:01.148 --> 01:26:03.358
help you make
fools of yourselves

1296
01:26:03.359 --> 01:26:06.145
all on your own.

1297
01:26:11.325 --> 01:26:12.359
No.

1298
01:26:14.370 --> 01:26:17.781
Your choices. Clark.

1299
01:26:18.415 --> 01:26:20.492
Your actions.

1300
01:26:22.294 --> 01:26:26.623
That's what makes you
who you are.

1301
01:26:28.217 --> 01:26:29.960
I'll tell you something. son.

1302
01:26:31.428 --> 01:26:33.047
I couldn't be…

1303
01:26:37.518 --> 01:26:40.054
…more proud of you.

1304
01:26:49.155 --> 01:26:50.606
Ol' mush.

1305
01:26:51.157 --> 01:26:53.817
Clark. there's something
on the box you might wanna see.

1306
01:26:57.204 --> 01:26:58.663
And over in Eastern Europe.

1307
01:26:58.664 --> 01:27:00.540
Boravian troops
gather at the border.

1308
01:27:00.541 --> 01:27:02.083
seemingly mere minutes away

1309
01:27:02.084 --> 01:27:04.419
from invading
Jarhanpur once again.

1310
01:27:04.420 --> 01:27:06.337
Now.
nearby villagers are willing

1311
01:27:06.338 --> 01:27:07.797
and ready
to defend their country.

1312
01:27:07.798 --> 01:27:11.509
despite the exponentially
superior firepower

1313
01:27:11.510 --> 01:27:13.587
of the well-trained Boravian military.

1314
01:27:28.444 --> 01:27:29.777
The villagers cling onto

1315
01:27:29.778 --> 01:27:31.522
what little hope they have left.

1316
01:27:31.655 --> 01:27:33.816
as they're surrounded
by the military.

1317
01:27:33.991 --> 01:27:37.076
Boravian president.
Vasil Ghurkos. says the invasion

1318
01:27:37.077 --> 01:27:38.745
is to protect
the Jarhanpurian people

1319
01:27:38.746 --> 01:27:40.322
from a tyrannical government.

1320
01:27:48.923 --> 01:27:51.483
Superman! Superman!

1321
01:27:52.084 --> 01:27:54.894
Superman! Superman!

1322
01:27:55.295 --> 01:27:57.147
Superman! Superman!

1323
01:27:57.548 --> 01:27:59.858
Superman! Superman!

1324
01:28:00.259 --> 01:28:02.193
Superman! Superman!

1325
01:28:02.594 --> 01:28:05.880
Superman! Superman! Superman!

1326
01:28:06.181 --> 01:28:10.110
Superman! Superman! Superman!

1327
01:28:12.488 --> 01:28:15.073
Without Superman
here to stop it this time.

1328
01:28:15.074 --> 01:28:18.068
the Jarhanpurians don't have much hope.

1329
01:28:18.410 --> 01:28:21.447
I cleaned your boots.
I'll go get 'em for you.

1330
01:28:22.873 --> 01:28:23.957
Superman.

1331
01:28:23.958 --> 01:28:25.917
We need you here in Metropolis now.

1332
01:28:25.918 --> 01:28:27.377
I have to get to Boravia. Terrific.

1333
01:28:27.378 --> 01:28:29.712
There won't be a Boravia.
or a Metropolis.

1334
01:28:29.713 --> 01:28:32.082
or a Planet Earth.
if you don't get here soon.

1335
01:28:32.883 --> 01:28:34.634
This rift is about to
tear into the city.

1336
01:28:34.635 --> 01:28:37.546
I can't stop it.
I need your help.

1337
01:28:40.099 --> 01:28:41.975
All Metropolis citizens.

1338
01:28:41.976 --> 01:28:44.686
This is a mandatory evacuation.

1339
01:28:44.687 --> 01:28:48.057
Repeat: this evacuation
is not optional.

1340
01:28:49.650 --> 01:28:52.235
This is a mandatory evacuation.

1341
01:28:52.236 --> 01:28:56.273
Repeat:
this evacuation is not optional.

1342
01:28:58.659 --> 01:29:01.403
This is a mandatory evacuation.

1343
01:29:08.335 --> 01:29:10.378
Yeah. I'm sure
she's scared. but find her.

1344
01:29:10.379 --> 01:29:11.914
Yeah. we're all equally scared.

1345
01:29:12.464 --> 01:29:14.249
Come on. just put her on.

1346
01:29:14.758 --> 01:29:17.252
Please. Juanita. can you put
Persephone on the phone?

1347
01:29:17.761 --> 01:29:20.471
Yes. she will care! Cats
know the sound of your voice!

1348
01:29:20.472 --> 01:29:23.050
So. I was able to connect
with our contact at BodaBank.

1349
01:29:23.225 --> 01:29:24.726
Luthor's been
selling arms to Ghurkos

1350
01:29:24.727 --> 01:29:27.020
for pennies
on the dollar for years.

1351
01:29:27.021 --> 01:29:29.640
- Why. you ask?
- I do ask why.

1352
01:29:29.899 --> 01:29:33.484
He did it in exchange
for half of Jarhanpur.

1353
01:29:33.485 --> 01:29:34.502
You're kidding.

1354
01:29:34.503 --> 01:29:36.779
At first. I thought Eve
was just sending me selfies.

1355
01:29:36.780 --> 01:29:38.865
But in the background
of the shots

1356
01:29:38.866 --> 01:29:40.617
are maps. contracts.

1357
01:29:40.618 --> 01:29:43.161
all kinds of documents
chronicling Boravia's agreement

1358
01:29:43.162 --> 01:29:44.996
to cede half of the country
to Lex Luthor

1359
01:29:44.997 --> 01:29:46.789
once the invasion is complete.

1360
01:29:46.790 --> 01:29:48.367
He wants to make himself king.

1361
01:29:48.667 --> 01:29:50.577
- King?
- King.

1362
01:29:50.836 --> 01:29:52.788
Should we really
still be standing here?

1363
01:29:53.339 --> 01:29:55.548
Lois. you got that flying
saucer deal up on the roof?

1364
01:29:55.549 --> 01:29:58.384
- Yup.
- Grant. Troupe.

1365
01:29:58.385 --> 01:29:59.928
- Come on.
- Grab the board. Jimmy.

1366
01:29:59.929 --> 01:30:02.931
- How many does it hold?
- Five. or six. Six.

1367
01:30:02.932 --> 01:30:06.434
- Okay. Lombard. you too.
- Oh. thank you.

1368
01:30:06.435 --> 01:30:08.770
Why the hell would Lex
want half a desert?

1369
01:30:08.771 --> 01:30:10.580
His cultish acolytes believe
he's gonna create

1370
01:30:10.581 --> 01:30:12.524
a technologically advanced utopia.

1371
01:30:12.525 --> 01:30:13.558
Utopia?

1372
01:30:13.559 --> 01:30:14.926
There's a profit factor as well.

1373
01:30:14.927 --> 01:30:18.112
I mean. the petroleum deposits alone
are worth multiples of his investment.

1374
01:30:18.113 --> 01:30:19.489
Whatever his motives are.

1375
01:30:19.490 --> 01:30:22.325
we know Luthor did everything he could
to ruin Superman's reputation.

1376
01:30:22.326 --> 01:30:23.409
Eve's photos show

1377
01:30:23.410 --> 01:30:25.829
he was behind the whole
Hammer of Boravia scam.

1378
01:30:25.830 --> 01:30:27.205
And all the bots stirring up

1379
01:30:27.206 --> 01:30:28.957
anti-Superman sentiment online.

1380
01:30:28.958 --> 01:30:31.876
Mr. Terrific believes
Luthor is also behind

1381
01:30:31.877 --> 01:30:34.379
the spreading rift
between universes out there.

1382
01:30:34.380 --> 01:30:36.481
All of it seems to be geared
toward stopping Superman

1383
01:30:36.482 --> 01:30:38.892
from standing in the way
of the Boravian invasion. Chief.

1384
01:30:39.134 --> 01:30:42.171
Call me Perry. kid. Post the story. Fast.

1385
01:30:47.810 --> 01:30:49.619
- Buckle up. kids.
- Why don't I have a seat?

1386
01:30:49.620 --> 01:30:51.697
- Jimmy. will you transcribe?
- Uh-huh.

1387
01:30:58.195 --> 01:31:00.105
Oh. God!

1388
01:31:04.451 --> 01:31:06.911
The Daily Planet has
obtained exclusive information

1389
01:31:06.912 --> 01:31:09.038
proving that billionaire
Lex Luthor is in league

1390
01:31:09.039 --> 01:31:11.492
with Boravian dictator.
Vasil Ghurkos.

1391
01:31:19.258 --> 01:31:20.884
Clark. are you close?

1392
01:31:20.885 --> 01:31:22.468
It's about to hit Metropolis.

1393
01:31:22.469 --> 01:31:24.171
and my codes
are not shutting it down.

1394
01:31:25.097 --> 01:31:26.382
Shit!

1395
01:31:43.782 --> 01:31:44.817
Uh-oh.

1396
01:31:52.374 --> 01:31:55.251
Lex! The rift is almost here!

1397
01:31:55.252 --> 01:31:56.878
So slow it down.

1398
01:31:56.879 --> 01:31:58.830
I can't unless I can
put the code in to stop it.

1399
01:31:58.831 --> 01:32:00.265
Hold on a minute then.

1400
01:32:00.674 --> 01:32:03.335
- We gotta go. man!
- Otis!

1401
01:32:23.113 --> 01:32:25.649
Not sure where we're gonna land
when the world is gone.

1402
01:33:25.476 --> 01:33:26.801
There's a code to close the rift.

1403
01:33:26.802 --> 01:33:28.629
but it's too complicated
to hack.

1404
01:33:28.721 --> 01:33:30.889
Luthor will have the code
at LuthorCorp.

1405
01:33:30.890 --> 01:33:33.032
Just give me a minute.
I'll get Krypto. and we'll go--

1406
01:33:33.033 --> 01:33:34.601
You brought that dog. man?

1407
01:33:34.602 --> 01:33:37.971
Yeah. I didn't-- didn't want him
killing my parents' cows.

1408
01:33:57.675 --> 01:33:58.750
Go on wide.

1409
01:33:58.751 --> 01:33:59.959
Wrong.
Focus on The Engineer.

1410
01:33:59.960 --> 01:34:01.954
- I'm on the alien. Larry.
- 7R.

1411
01:34:21.424 --> 01:34:22.899
It's not too late for either of you.

1412
01:34:22.900 --> 01:34:23.933
5A!

1413
01:34:23.934 --> 01:34:25.510
You don't have to do
what Luthor--

1414
01:34:48.634 --> 01:34:50.294
2X!

1415
01:34:56.058 --> 01:34:57.892
Now. Angela. as planned.

1416
01:34:57.893 --> 01:35:00.637
fill his lungs
and kill the son of a bitch.

1417
01:35:42.688 --> 01:35:45.231
Can't he hold his breath
for over an hour?

1418
01:35:45.232 --> 01:35:47.108
Not without air in his lungs.

1419
01:35:47.109 --> 01:35:48.443
He'll be dead in minutes.

1420
01:35:48.444 --> 01:35:50.211
The nanites
are suppressing his optic nerve.

1421
01:35:50.212 --> 01:35:52.447
Sight and X-ray vision
should be completely muted.

1422
01:35:52.448 --> 01:35:53.774
Lungs breached.

1423
01:35:59.538 --> 01:36:01.532
Da?

1424
01:36:04.793 --> 01:36:07.996
We will not sleep

1425
01:36:08.422 --> 01:36:11.966
until the street is flooded

1426
01:36:11.967 --> 01:36:16.755
with the blood of every Jarhanpurian!

1427
01:36:51.799 --> 01:36:53.417
What's his game?

1428
01:36:54.552 --> 01:36:56.761
Using friction
to get the nanites off?

1429
01:36:56.762 --> 01:36:58.529
Doesn't matter
if he gets them off his face.

1430
01:36:58.530 --> 01:37:00.239
The nanites
are still in his lungs.

1431
01:37:00.240 --> 01:37:02.058
Engineer. Ultraman. keep up.

1432
01:37:02.059 --> 01:37:03.886
We're trying.

1433
01:37:07.857 --> 01:37:09.858
- Maintain LOS.
- Yes. No shit. Larry.

1434
01:37:09.859 --> 01:37:10.859
Hurry.

1435
01:37:31.046 --> 01:37:32.498
He'll suffocate any minute.

1436
01:37:40.347 --> 01:37:42.508
Engineer. envelop him completely.

1437
01:38:08.959 --> 01:38:10.994
Wait! Wait. wait!
What is he doing?

1438
01:38:18.260 --> 01:38:21.922
I won't be able to sustain
the impact at this speed.

1439
01:38:23.807 --> 01:38:26.802
No. Angela. unsheathe!
He's the only one protected!

1440
01:38:43.536 --> 01:38:47.698
Entering the hole. Infrared. please?

1441
01:38:54.255 --> 01:38:56.040
Switch to night vision.

1442
01:38:59.760 --> 01:39:00.878
Whoa.

1443
01:39:28.372 --> 01:39:30.824
Her heart's still beating.
but she's unconscious.

1444
01:39:31.125 --> 01:39:32.326
Call in the Raptors.

1445
01:39:59.737 --> 01:40:01.613
What the hell?

1446
01:40:01.614 --> 01:40:05.575
That's right. Cloning you
was relatively simple.

1447
01:40:05.576 --> 01:40:08.369
All it took was combing
the aftermath of your battles…

1448
01:40:08.370 --> 01:40:10.330
…until I
located a strand of your hair.

1449
01:40:10.331 --> 01:40:13.082
That's how you got
into the Fortress.

1450
01:40:13.083 --> 01:40:14.451
You had my DNA.

1451
01:40:14.543 --> 01:40:17.545
Yes. but as is often the case
with cloning.

1452
01:40:17.546 --> 01:40:18.880
the match was imperfect.

1453
01:40:18.881 --> 01:40:23.384
He might be even stupider
than you. If that's possible.

1454
01:40:23.385 --> 01:40:24.802
But easier to control.

1455
01:40:24.803 --> 01:40:27.089
- 3L.
- And stronger.

1456
01:40:28.224 --> 01:40:29.341
22K!

1457
01:40:32.102 --> 01:40:33.303
31D!

1458
01:40:34.063 --> 01:40:35.139
2A!

1459
01:40:36.065 --> 01:40:37.808
5B! 5B!

1460
01:40:38.484 --> 01:40:40.602
6K! 9A!

1461
01:40:42.112 --> 01:40:44.781
My brain will always win!

1462
01:40:44.782 --> 01:40:47.735
Brain beats brawn!

1463
01:41:39.295 --> 01:41:41.805
Superman. Superman.

1464
01:41:42.206 --> 01:41:44.833
Superman. Superman.

1465
01:41:50.097 --> 01:41:52.091
No matter what you do to me.
Luthor.

1466
01:41:53.058 --> 01:41:54.934
your plans in Boravia
won't work.

1467
01:41:54.935 --> 01:41:57.846
Oh. really? Why's that?

1468
01:41:58.022 --> 01:41:59.973
'Cause I called in some friends.

1469
01:42:00.357 --> 01:42:01.767
Mr. Luthor?

1470
01:42:02.902 --> 01:42:04.812
There is an anomaly
at the border.

1471
01:42:17.374 --> 01:42:18.742
Sorry. kid.

1472
01:42:19.084 --> 01:42:20.661
Superman couldn't make it.

1473
01:42:21.378 --> 01:42:23.080
So you got an upgrade.

1474
01:42:49.657 --> 01:42:52.526
Our forces aren't prepared
to deal with metahuman anomalies.

1475
01:42:52.785 --> 01:42:54.494
I've sent the word to retreat.

1476
01:42:54.495 --> 01:42:55.863
Retreat?!

1477
01:42:55.913 --> 01:42:57.580
No! No! No!

1478
01:42:57.581 --> 01:42:59.324
We must get to the bunker!

1479
01:42:59.375 --> 01:43:00.409
The bunker!

1480
01:43:17.017 --> 01:43:19.053
I know you won't kill me.

1481
01:43:19.353 --> 01:43:23.565
You are too delicate and weak.
like Superman.

1482
01:43:23.566 --> 01:43:26.018
I'm not like Superman.

1483
01:43:33.367 --> 01:43:35.861
- It's perfect. Post it. kid.
- On it.

1484
01:43:42.084 --> 01:43:44.002
I think you overestimate
the importance

1485
01:43:44.003 --> 01:43:46.546
of Jarhanpur to me. Superman.

1486
01:43:46.547 --> 01:43:48.248
That was just a bonus.

1487
01:43:48.716 --> 01:43:50.216
I'm not killing you

1488
01:43:50.217 --> 01:43:54.004
so the Boravian military
conflict can proceed.

1489
01:43:54.305 --> 01:43:58.558
I created
the Boravian military conflict

1490
01:43:58.559 --> 01:44:02.930
so I'd have an excuse
to kill you!

1491
01:44:03.105 --> 01:44:04.939
Once you involved yourself.

1492
01:44:04.940 --> 01:44:06.399
I knew I could easily get

1493
01:44:06.400 --> 01:44:08.560
our government's
support in nullifying you.

1494
01:44:08.944 --> 01:44:09.978
Why?

1495
01:44:10.362 --> 01:44:13.114
Because you're destroying us!

1496
01:44:13.115 --> 01:44:15.025
10Y. 13B.

1497
01:44:36.222 --> 01:44:38.006
You're driven by envy. Luthor.

1498
01:44:38.265 --> 01:44:42.101
- You couldn't be more obvious.
- No shit. I'm not dim.

1499
01:44:42.102 --> 01:44:45.313
I'm aware envy consumes
my every waking moment.

1500
01:44:45.314 --> 01:44:46.473
13L.

1501
01:44:49.677 --> 01:44:52.512
I know when they mention
Galileo or Einstein

1502
01:44:52.513 --> 01:44:54.614
or one of these other twits
in the same breath as me.

1503
01:44:54.615 --> 01:44:57.367
I feel a tide of vomit
burn the back of my throat.

1504
01:44:57.368 --> 01:44:58.743
But at least Galileo
did something.

1505
01:44:58.744 --> 01:45:02.489
He wasn't some dopey Venusian
catapulted onto this planet.

1506
01:45:02.706 --> 01:45:05.667
just to have the world
fawn over him.

1507
01:45:05.668 --> 01:45:10.664
because his strength illuminates
how weak we all really are.

1508
01:45:14.844 --> 01:45:18.179
So. my envy is a calling.

1509
01:45:18.180 --> 01:45:21.391
It is the sole hope for humanity.

1510
01:45:21.392 --> 01:45:26.187
because it is what has driven me
to annihilating you.

1511
01:45:26.188 --> 01:45:27.389
1A!

1512
01:45:27.523 --> 01:45:29.983
1A! 1A!

1513
01:45:29.984 --> 01:45:33.278
1A! 1A! 1A! 1A!

1514
01:45:33.279 --> 01:45:34.279
Yes.

1515
01:45:43.330 --> 01:45:47.117
Oh. what are you smirking at.
you idiot?

1516
01:45:47.293 --> 01:45:51.455
Brain beats brawn.

1517
01:45:52.798 --> 01:45:53.999
Sorry. chum.

1518
01:46:10.566 --> 01:46:11.975
No. no. no! No!

1519
01:46:16.363 --> 01:46:19.733
You watch him through those?
Tell him what to do?

1520
01:46:27.541 --> 01:46:28.867
Krypto.

1521
01:46:30.169 --> 01:46:31.286
Get the toy.

1522
01:46:34.381 --> 01:46:37.084
Uh. thir-thirty-s--
Oh. the stupid dog!

1523
01:46:37.301 --> 01:46:38.794
- Uh…
- Charlie down!

1524
01:46:52.149 --> 01:46:54.268
- 12C! Aah!
- Delta down.

1525
01:47:00.157 --> 01:47:01.358
36B--

1526
01:47:02.284 --> 01:47:03.485
- No.
- Hotel down!

1527
01:47:11.085 --> 01:47:12.752
- No!
- Bravo down.

1528
01:47:12.753 --> 01:47:14.705
- Bravo down!
- I just said that. Larry!

1529
01:47:29.937 --> 01:47:31.388
Alpha down!

1530
01:47:33.107 --> 01:47:34.107
Lex.

1531
01:47:34.984 --> 01:47:36.810
The Raptors have arrived.

1532
01:47:42.116 --> 01:47:44.401
- Kill him!
- Good luck with that.

1533
01:48:49.183 --> 01:48:50.342
Hey!

1534
01:48:52.603 --> 01:48:55.855
This ain't playtime!
Quit messin' around!

1535
01:48:55.856 --> 01:48:57.899
We have to get to Luthor
to stop the rift.

1536
01:48:57.900 --> 01:48:59.150
I'm not messing around.

1537
01:48:59.151 --> 01:49:00.894
I'm doing important stuff.

1538
01:49:03.322 --> 01:49:05.524
It's gonna reach Bakerline
any minute.

1539
01:49:05.783 --> 01:49:07.317
There are people there.

1540
01:49:14.200 --> 01:49:16.084
- We have to go.
- We'll never make it in time.

1541
01:49:16.085 --> 01:49:18.105
- It's almost here.
- We have to try. Come on.

1542
01:49:21.715 --> 01:49:23.584
Lex!

1543
01:49:24.760 --> 01:49:26.135
I'm closing the freakin' rift.

1544
01:49:26.136 --> 01:49:28.888
No! They chose him!
Let them die!

1545
01:49:28.889 --> 01:49:30.890
-We'll close it from the bunker
-What?

1546
01:49:30.891 --> 01:49:32.760
…before it gets
to a city I care about.

1547
01:49:35.020 --> 01:49:36.472
Open the portal!

1548
01:49:41.235 --> 01:49:43.187
Wrap it up. Let's go.

1549
01:49:43.737 --> 01:49:45.481
Safety first. people.

1550
01:49:57.543 --> 01:50:00.454
Hey. Hey. The code
to close the rift is in here.

1551
01:50:01.088 --> 01:50:03.290
- I can help.
- I don't need your help.

1552
01:50:03.674 --> 01:50:05.793
I'm goddamn Mr. Terrific.

1553
01:50:06.802 --> 01:50:09.880
You piece of shit alien!

1554
01:50:10.931 --> 01:50:13.675
That is where you've always
been wrong about me. Lex.

1555
01:50:14.560 --> 01:50:16.352
I'm as human as anyone.

1556
01:50:16.353 --> 01:50:19.063
I love. I… I get scared.

1557
01:50:19.064 --> 01:50:21.816
I wake up every morning. and
despite not knowing what to do.

1558
01:50:21.817 --> 01:50:23.610
I put one foot
in front of the other.

1559
01:50:23.611 --> 01:50:25.945
and I try to make
the best choices I can.

1560
01:50:25.946 --> 01:50:27.822
I screw up all the time.

1561
01:50:27.823 --> 01:50:29.900
But that is being human.

1562
01:50:30.993 --> 01:50:33.028
And that's my greatest strength.

1563
01:50:34.246 --> 01:50:38.374
And someday I hope.
for the sake of the world.

1564
01:50:38.375 --> 01:50:40.460
you understand
that it's yours too.

1565
01:50:40.461 --> 01:50:43.004
Oh. that's beautiful.

1566
01:50:43.005 --> 01:50:46.257
But none of this matters.
you patronizing clown.

1567
01:50:46.258 --> 01:50:50.053
The government gave me
the authority to kill you.

1568
01:50:50.054 --> 01:50:51.930
If not today. then tomor--

1569
01:50:51.931 --> 01:50:53.090
Ahh!

1570
01:50:57.978 --> 01:50:59.229
No. no. no!

1571
01:50:59.230 --> 01:51:01.807
Oh. my-- Stop.
Krypto. put him down.

1572
01:51:04.401 --> 01:51:05.860
Krypto. drop him!

1573
01:51:05.861 --> 01:51:07.521
Krypto. drop him! Drop him!

1574
01:51:12.451 --> 01:51:14.403
Dude.

1575
01:51:19.875 --> 01:51:21.326
Got it.

1576
01:51:35.683 --> 01:51:37.634
Yes!

1577
01:51:46.485 --> 01:51:48.854
Mmm.

1578
01:51:49.405 --> 01:51:51.106
- Lex.
- What?

1579
01:51:51.699 --> 01:51:53.658
Well. this just in.
An absolute bombshell

1580
01:51:53.659 --> 01:51:55.076
from the Daily Planet.

1581
01:51:55.077 --> 01:51:57.328
Billionaire Lex Luthor
aligning himself

1582
01:51:57.329 --> 01:51:59.706
with a foreign entity.
believe it or not.

1583
01:51:59.707 --> 01:52:01.124
Luthor has been giving them

1584
01:52:01.125 --> 01:52:03.710
billions and billions of
dollars' worth of free weapons--

1585
01:52:03.711 --> 01:52:06.796
Lex Luthor has been working
covertly with Vasil Ghurkos

1586
01:52:06.797 --> 01:52:08.214
and the Boravian government

1587
01:52:08.215 --> 01:52:11.050
to overthrow
the country of Jarhanpur.

1588
01:52:11.051 --> 01:52:12.760
Luthor has been giving them
billions…

1589
01:52:12.761 --> 01:52:15.172
We've had Luthor
on this show many times.

1590
01:52:15.681 --> 01:52:17.758
Little did we know. he was a traitor.

1591
01:52:21.228 --> 01:52:22.270
Seems like the one thing

1592
01:52:22.271 --> 01:52:25.064
conservatives and liberals
can finally agree on

1593
01:52:25.065 --> 01:52:26.642
is that Lex Luthor sucks.

1594
01:52:26.859 --> 01:52:30.278
The whole world has
turned against Superman.

1595
01:52:30.279 --> 01:52:33.399
and we all owe him
an enormous apology.

1596
01:52:33.657 --> 01:52:37.945
He is. of course. the hero
we always thought he was.

1597
01:53:08.526 --> 01:53:11.311
Thank you! Thank you!

1598
01:53:16.700 --> 01:53:18.110
That was sick.

1599
01:53:18.619 --> 01:53:21.037
Guy. maybe
he should join the group.

1600
01:53:21.038 --> 01:53:22.622
Please.

1601
01:53:22.623 --> 01:53:25.416
I mean. no offense. but that
creepy mug is what you want

1602
01:53:25.417 --> 01:53:27.418
representing the Justice Gang?

1603
01:53:27.419 --> 01:53:28.620
Justice Gang?

1604
01:53:29.296 --> 01:53:30.789
That's a cool name.

1605
01:53:31.632 --> 01:53:32.632
You're in.

1606
01:53:35.427 --> 01:53:36.712
Come on!

1607
01:53:39.932 --> 01:53:41.015
Glad you're not concerned

1608
01:53:41.016 --> 01:53:42.468
about the metahumans. Rick.

1609
01:53:43.060 --> 01:53:45.471
'Cause now they're the ones
making the rules.

1610
01:53:57.366 --> 01:53:58.950
Everyone file. This way. please.

1611
01:53:58.951 --> 01:54:00.118
Easy!

1612
01:54:00.119 --> 01:54:03.155
- Fleurette!
- Mom!

1613
01:54:06.167 --> 01:54:07.368
Oh!

1614
01:54:11.213 --> 01:54:13.415
Get his bald ass to Belle Reve.

1615
01:54:50.503 --> 01:54:53.414
Oh!

1616
01:54:54.757 --> 01:54:57.167
Now we can be together forever.

1617
01:55:04.475 --> 01:55:05.475
Miss Lane.

1618
01:55:06.894 --> 01:55:09.221
Oh. hi.

1619
01:55:09.522 --> 01:55:11.557
I thought I might give you
an interview.

1620
01:55:12.107 --> 01:55:14.692
I could fill you in
on all of the behind-the-scenes.

1621
01:55:14.693 --> 01:55:15.769
Sure.

1622
01:55:16.445 --> 01:55:18.147
I think that would be…

1623
01:55:19.615 --> 01:55:20.615
great.

1624
01:55:22.243 --> 01:55:23.493
Um…

1625
01:55:23.494 --> 01:55:24.737
How about over here?

1626
01:55:24.912 --> 01:55:26.113
For an interview.

1627
01:55:59.321 --> 01:56:00.356
Hey.

1628
01:56:03.576 --> 01:56:04.985
I love you. too.

1629
01:56:32.188 --> 01:56:33.730
How long
have they been hooking up?

1630
01:56:33.731 --> 01:56:35.182
About three months. I think.

1631
01:56:40.154 --> 01:56:42.447
Got this place cleaned up
pretty good.

1632
01:56:42.448 --> 01:56:44.491
Cleaned yourself up
pretty good. too.

1633
01:56:44.492 --> 01:56:46.367
- You think so?
- Yeah.

1634
01:56:46.368 --> 01:56:47.820
Think it gives you character.

1635
01:56:48.621 --> 01:56:50.656
Maybe one day
you'll give me a name.

1636
01:56:51.123 --> 01:56:53.617
Well. Four's a name.

1637
01:56:53.918 --> 01:56:55.369
So is Gary.

1638
01:56:58.422 --> 01:57:00.006
Aw. shoot.

1639
01:57:00.007 --> 01:57:02.251
Sir. I think
your cousin has returned.

1640
01:57:04.512 --> 01:57:08.549
- Yup.
- What the hell. dude?

1641
01:57:09.350 --> 01:57:11.059
Why did you move the door?

1642
01:57:11.060 --> 01:57:13.762
- I didn't move the door.
- Where is my dog?

1643
01:57:21.153 --> 01:57:23.696
Okay. well. this is why
he has behavioral issues.

1644
01:57:23.697 --> 01:57:25.190
No boundaries.

1645
01:57:28.452 --> 01:57:30.612
- It's not healthy. is it?
- Mm-mmm.

1646
01:57:39.880 --> 01:57:41.130
Come on.

1647
01:57:41.131 --> 01:57:43.459
Thanks for watching him. bitch.

1648
01:57:46.637 --> 01:57:49.222
She likes to go and party
on other planets.

1649
01:57:49.223 --> 01:57:51.349
- Planets with red suns.
- Oh.

1650
01:57:51.350 --> 01:57:52.725
Because of our metabolism.

1651
01:57:52.726 --> 01:57:55.270
we can't get drunk
on a planet with a yellow sun.

1652
01:57:55.271 --> 01:57:57.730
If I had any emotional capacity
whatsoever.

1653
01:57:57.731 --> 01:57:59.892
I'd be concerned
about her partying.

1654
01:57:59.984 --> 01:58:00.984
Yeah.

1655
01:58:01.068 --> 01:58:04.529
Superman. would you like to see
the footage of your parents?

1656
01:58:04.530 --> 01:58:07.191
- He finds it soothing.
- Oh!

1657
01:58:07.449 --> 01:58:09.485
Yeah. Gary. that'd be nice.

1658
01:58:16.333 --> 01:58:17.333
Everything you see.

1659
01:58:17.334 --> 01:58:18.869
you're seeing for the first time.

1660
01:58:26.051 --> 01:58:27.594
All of this is for you.

1661
01:58:30.890 --> 01:58:32.007
Clark.

1662
01:58:42.151 --> 01:58:43.352
You did it!

1663
02:08:30.865 --> 02:08:31.899
Hmm.

1664
02:08:33.200 --> 02:08:34.318
What?

1665
02:08:38.038 --> 02:08:39.038
Yeah?

1666
02:08:39.165 --> 02:08:41.249
It's just… a little off.

1667
02:08:41.250 --> 02:08:42.584
What do you want me to do?

1668
02:08:42.585 --> 02:08:44.844
Do you want me to take it apart
and put it back together?

1669
02:08:44.845 --> 02:08:46.446
No. no. no. no. I was just…

1670
02:08:47.923 --> 02:08:49.041
You just what?

1671
02:08:51.427 --> 02:08:53.504
Hey. man. I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to bum you out.

1672
02:08:55.222 --> 02:08:56.799
I shouldn't have brought it up.

1673
02:08:57.800 --> 02:09:00.600
Darn it.
I can be such a jerk sometimes.
